AND SPECIAL EFFECTS.

6
00:00:29,810 --> 00:00:31,820
WHILE THE WORLD
HE INHABITS...

7
00:00:32,030 --> 00:00:34,820
IS, IN SOME RESPECTS,
COUNTERFEIT,

8
00:00:35,490 --> 00:00:38,410
THERE'S NOTHING FAKE
ABOUT TRUMAN HIMSELF--

9
00:00:39,660 --> 00:00:40,830
NO SCRIPTS,

10
00:00:41,030 --> 00:00:42,160
  NO CUE CARDS.

11
00:00:42,370 --> 00:00:45,370
IT ISN'T ALWAYS SHAKESPEARE,
BUT IT'S GENUINE.

12
00:00:46,960 --> 00:00:49,330
IT'S A LIFE.

13
00:00:51,880 --> 00:00:54,130
I'M NOT GOING TO MAKE IT.

14
00:00:54,340 --> 00:00:57,220
YOU'RE GOING TO HAVE
TO GO ON WITHOUT ME.

15
00:01:02,350 --> 00:01:04,060
NO WAY, MISTER.

16
00:01:04,270 --> 00:01:06,810
YOU'RE GOING TO THE TOP
OF THIS MOUNTAIN,

17
00:01:07,020 --> 00:01:09,520
BROKEN LEGS AND ALL.

18
00:01:12,480 --> 00:01:14,480
WE FIND MANY VIEWERS
LEAVE HIM ON

19
00:01:14,690 --> 00:01:17,200
ALL NIGHT FOR COMFORT.

20
00:01:18,070 --> 00:01:20,780
YOU'RE CRAZY,
YOU KNOW THAT?

21
00:01:23,160 --> 00:01:24,830
WELL, FOR ME,
THERE IS NO DIFFERENCE

22
00:01:25,040 --> 00:01:26,910
BETWEEN A PRIVATE LIFE
AND A PUBLIC LIFE.

23
00:01:27,120 --> 00:01:30,210
  MY LIFE...IS MY LIFE,
IS  THE TRUMAN SHOW.

24
00:01:30,380 --> 00:01:33,500
  THE TRUMAN SHOW
IS...   A LIFESTYLE.

25
00:01:33,800 --> 00:01:35,130
IT'S A NOBLE LIFE.

26
00:01:35,340 --> 00:01:37,630
IT IS...

27
00:01:38,930 --> 00:01:39,630
A TRULY BLESSED LIFE.

28
00:01:39,840 --> 00:01:43,050
  YEAH, TELL ME SOMETHING
I  DON'T   KNOW.

29
00:01:44,100 --> 00:01:46,980
ALL RIGHT. PROMISE ME
ONE THING, THOUGH.

30
00:01:48,060 --> 00:01:50,900
IF I DIE BEFORE I REACH
THE SUMMIT,

31
00:01:51,100 --> 00:01:54,110
YOU'LL USE ME AS
AN ALTERNATIVE SOURCE OF FOOD.

32
00:01:54,940 --> 00:01:57,280
EW. GROSS.

33
00:01:59,650 --> 00:02:02,120
IT'S ALL TRUE.
IT'S ALL REAL.

34
00:02:02,320 --> 00:02:02,820
NOTHING HERE IS FAKE.

35
00:02:03,030 --> 00:02:05,910
NOTHING YOU SEE
ON THIS SHOW IS FAKE.

36
00:02:06,120 --> 00:02:08,660
IT'S MERELY CONTROLLED.

37
00:02:15,670 --> 00:02:18,090
EAT ME, DAMN IT.

38
00:02:18,090 --> 00:02:20,510
THAT'S AN ORDER.

39
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:24,470
MAYBE JUST
YOUR LOVE HANDLES.

40
00:02:24,760 --> 00:02:26,640
I HAVE LOVE HANDLES?

41
00:02:26,850 --> 00:02:27,810
YEAH.

42
00:02:28,020 --> 00:02:28,810
LITTLE ONES.

43
00:02:29,020 --> 00:02:29,680
Meryl: TRUMAN!

44
00:02:29,890 --> 00:02:32,100
YOU'RE GOING
TO BE LATE.

45
00:02:32,310 --> 00:02:34,520
OK!

46
00:02:36,020 --> 00:02:38,320
[SIGHS]

47
00:02:43,320 --> 00:02:45,780
[BIRDS TWITTER]

48
00:02:47,790 --> 00:02:48,450
GOOD MORNING.

49
00:02:48,660 --> 00:02:50,000
MORNING.
MORNING.

50
00:02:50,210 --> 00:02:51,870
OH, AND IN CASE
I DON'T SEE YOU,

51
00:02:52,080 --> 00:02:53,290
GOOD AFTERNOON,
GOOD EVENING,

52
00:02:53,500 --> 00:02:54,630
AND GOOD NIGHT.

53
00:02:54,840 --> 00:02:55,840
[ALL LAUGH]

54
00:02:56,040 --> 00:02:57,090
Truman: YEP, YEP.

55
00:02:57,300 --> 00:02:58,670
MORNING.
MORNING, SPENCER.

56
00:02:58,880 --> 00:02:59,800
[BARKS]
HEY, PLUTO.

57
00:03:00,010 --> 00:03:01,090
NO, NO, NO.
GET DOWN.

58
00:03:01,300 --> 00:03:02,130
Spencer:
HE WON'T HURT YOU.

59
00:03:02,340 --> 00:03:04,970
GET DOWN.
HA HA. I KNOW.

60
00:03:05,100 --> 00:03:05,930
IT'S JUST ME.

61
00:03:06,140 --> 00:03:08,270
COME ON, PLUTO.

62
00:03:08,470 --> 00:03:09,470
[BARKS]

63
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:11,940
OHH!

64
00:03:19,230 --> 00:03:21,570
HOLY COW.

65
00:03:29,700 --> 00:03:32,080
WHAT IS IT?

66
00:03:51,390 --> 00:03:52,890
Radio: HERE'S
A NEWS FLASH JUST IN.

67
00:03:53,100 --> 00:03:55,440
AN AIRCRAFT IN TROUBLE
BEGAN SHEDDING PARTS

68
00:03:55,650 --> 00:03:58,650
AS IT FLEW OVER SEAHAVEN
JUST A FEW MOMENTS AGO.

69
00:03:58,650 --> 00:03:59,020
I KNOW.

70
00:03:59,230 --> 00:04:00,690
WOW. LUCKILY,
NO ONE WAS HURT.

71
00:04:00,900 --> 00:04:02,570
BUT, HEY,
HOW DO YOU FEEL TODAY?

72
00:04:02,780 --> 00:04:03,400
MMM, MMM.

73
00:04:03,610 --> 00:04:04,110
HEH HEH. THAT'S GOOD.

74
00:04:04,320 --> 00:04:05,530
YOU THINKING OF
FLYING SOMEWHERE?

75
00:04:05,740 --> 00:04:07,410
NOPE.
NO? GOOD.

76
00:04:07,620 --> 00:04:08,740
THIS IS CLASSICAL CLIVE
WITH CLASSICAL DRIVE,

77
00:04:08,950 --> 00:04:11,580
SO WHY DON'T YOU FORGET
ABOUT THE PERILS OF FLYING,

78
00:04:11,790 --> 00:04:14,750
SETTLE BACK, AND LET
THIS MUSIC CALM YOU DOWN?

79
00:04:14,870 --> 00:04:17,580
[CLASSICAL
PIANO MUSIC PLAYS]

80
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:20,920
  DOG FANCY,  PLEASE.

81
00:04:21,130 --> 00:04:22,340
  DOG FANCY.

82
00:04:22,550 --> 00:04:24,050
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

83
00:04:24,260 --> 00:04:24,930
Truman: AHH!

84
00:04:25,130 --> 00:04:26,890
GIVE ME A PAPER THERE,
WILL YOU, EARL?

85
00:04:27,090 --> 00:04:28,350
OH, AND, UH...

86
00:04:28,550 --> 00:04:31,220
ONE OF THESE
FOR THE WIFE.

87
00:04:31,470 --> 00:04:32,810
LOVES
HER FASHION MAGS.

88
00:04:33,020 --> 00:04:33,850
WILL THAT BE ALL
FOR YOU, TRUMAN?

89
00:04:34,060 --> 00:04:35,810
THAT'S THE WHOLE
KIT AND CABOODLE.

90
00:04:36,020 --> 00:04:38,020
CATCH YOU LATER.
OK.

91
00:04:38,230 --> 00:04:40,440
YEP.

92
00:04:45,990 --> 00:04:46,990
Man: GOOD MORNING.

93
00:04:47,200 --> 00:04:48,160
HEY.

94
00:04:48,370 --> 00:04:48,990
HANK.

95
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:50,660
MORNING, TRUMAN.

96
00:04:50,870 --> 00:04:52,370
Both:
GOOD MORNING, TRUMAN.

97
00:04:52,580 --> 00:04:53,410
HEY, HOW ARE YOU, GUYS?

98
00:04:53,620 --> 00:04:54,700
BEAUTIFUL DAY,
ISN'T IT?

99
00:04:54,910 --> 00:04:55,410
OH. ALWAYS.

100
00:04:55,620 --> 00:04:58,420
OH, AND HOW'S
YOUR LOVELY WIFE?

101
00:04:58,960 --> 00:05:00,090
GOOD, GOOD.
HOW ABOUT YOURS?

102
00:05:00,290 --> 00:05:01,710
OH, COULDN'T BE BETTER.

103
00:05:01,920 --> 00:05:02,750
FINE, FINE, FINE.

104
00:05:02,960 --> 00:05:05,130
UM, NICE TALKING
TO YOU, TRUMAN.

105
00:05:05,340 --> 00:05:06,090
YOU, TOO.
WE MUST GO NOW.

106
00:05:06,300 --> 00:05:07,630
HEY, THINK ABOUT
THAT POLICY, HUH?

107
00:05:07,840 --> 00:05:10,430
OK, THAT'S 2 FOR 1.
THAT'S A GOOD DEAL.

108
00:05:10,640 --> 00:05:11,560
DOPPELGANGER SPECIAL.

109
00:05:11,760 --> 00:05:12,560
Twins: RIGHT.

110
00:05:12,760 --> 00:05:15,140
HEY.
HI.

111
00:05:16,270 --> 00:05:18,140
HEY, FELLAS.
YOU GOING IN?

112
00:05:18,350 --> 00:05:20,060
GO AHEAD.

113
00:05:20,270 --> 00:05:20,940
HEY.
GO AHEAD.

114
00:05:21,150 --> 00:05:22,360
NO, YOU FIRST,
PLEASE.

115
00:05:22,570 --> 00:05:25,360
I'M NOT THAT ANXIOUS
TO GET THERE.

116
00:05:25,490 --> 00:05:27,740
OHH...

117
00:05:27,900 --> 00:05:30,700
[WORKERS CHATTER,
TELEPHONES RING]

118
00:05:39,790 --> 00:05:40,330
[SOFTLY]
YES, HELLO.

119
00:05:40,540 --> 00:05:43,590
COULD I HAVE DIRECTORY
ASSISTANCE FOR FIJI, PLEASE?

120
00:05:44,210 --> 00:05:44,750
FIJI ISLANDS.

121
00:05:44,960 --> 00:05:47,340
TRUMAN,
DID YOU SEE THIS?

122
00:05:47,550 --> 00:05:48,010
HA!

123
00:05:48,220 --> 00:05:49,300
UH, I'M SORRY, MA'AM.

124
00:05:49,510 --> 00:05:52,510
IF--IF HE'S IN A COMA,
HE'S PROBABLY UNINSURABLE.

125
00:05:54,760 --> 00:05:55,520
[SOFTLY]
HELLO?

126
00:05:55,720 --> 00:05:56,930
YES. UH, FIJI, PLEASE.

127
00:05:57,140 --> 00:06:00,100
DO YOU HAVE A LISTING
FOR LAUREN GARLAND?

128
00:06:02,110 --> 00:06:04,520
NOTHING LISTED?

129
00:06:04,610 --> 00:06:04,940
OK.

130
00:06:05,150 --> 00:06:07,490
DO YOU HAVE
A SYLVIA GARLAND?

131
00:06:07,690 --> 00:06:10,160
"S" FOR SYLVIA.

132
00:06:11,320 --> 00:06:13,620
NOTHING?

133
00:06:14,120 --> 00:06:16,500
OK. THANK YOU.

134
00:06:39,230 --> 00:06:41,520
[COUGHS]

135
00:06:42,230 --> 00:06:44,520
[COUGHS]

136
00:06:50,950 --> 00:06:52,070
LAWRENCE.
HEY, BURBANK.

137
00:06:52,280 --> 00:06:54,990
GOT A PROSPECT
IN WELLS PARK

138
00:06:55,080 --> 00:06:57,580
I NEED YOU TO CLOSE.

139
00:06:58,790 --> 00:07:00,750
W-WELLS PARK?

140
00:07:00,960 --> 00:07:02,330
ON, UH...

141
00:07:02,540 --> 00:07:03,750
HARBOR ISLAND?

142
00:07:03,960 --> 00:07:05,790
YOU KNOW ANOTHER ONE?

143
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:07,340
WELL, I CAN'T DO IT.

144
00:07:07,550 --> 00:07:09,210
I, UH, HAVE
AN APPOINTMENT.

145
00:07:09,420 --> 00:07:11,550
DENTIST. OR...
YEAH.

146
00:07:11,760 --> 00:07:13,430
YOU'RE GOING TO LOSE
A LOT MORE THAN YOUR TEETH

147
00:07:13,640 --> 00:07:15,970
IF YOU DON'T MEET
YOUR QUOTA.

148
00:07:16,180 --> 00:07:16,560
LOOK, TRUMAN...

149
00:07:16,760 --> 00:07:19,810
THEY'RE MAKING CUTBACKS
AT THE END OF THIS MONTH.

150
00:07:20,520 --> 00:07:21,100
CUTBACKS?

151
00:07:21,310 --> 00:07:23,440
YEAH.
NOW, YOU NEED THIS.

152
00:07:23,650 --> 00:07:25,230
BESIDES, A HALF HOUR
ACROSS THE BAY,

153
00:07:25,440 --> 00:07:26,940
A LITTLE SEA AIR...

154
00:07:27,150 --> 00:07:29,610
WOULD DO YOU GOOD.

155
00:07:29,650 --> 00:07:30,360
HEY, THANKS.

156
00:07:30,570 --> 00:07:33,070
[SNAPS FINGERS]

157
00:07:40,620 --> 00:07:41,540
HELLO.

158
00:07:41,750 --> 00:07:42,660
FERRY STILL HERE, HUH?

159
00:07:42,870 --> 00:07:45,170
THOUGHT I MIGHT HAVE
MISSED IT.

160
00:07:45,380 --> 00:07:47,840
ONE-WAY OR RETURN?

161
00:07:48,040 --> 00:07:50,340
RETURN.

162
00:07:51,720 --> 00:07:53,130
THERE YOU GO, SIR.

163
00:07:53,340 --> 00:07:55,640
HEH HEH.

164
00:07:56,800 --> 00:07:59,510
[SHUTTERS OPEN
ELECTRONICALLY]

165
00:08:08,820 --> 00:08:11,110
[SIGHS]

166
00:08:33,300 --> 00:08:35,590
[SHUDDERS]

167
00:08:47,230 --> 00:08:49,520
UHH...

168
00:08:50,690 --> 00:08:52,190
DO YOU NEED
ANY HELP, SIR?

169
00:08:52,400 --> 00:08:55,150
YOU GO AHEAD.
I'LL--I'LL BE FINE.

170
00:08:56,320 --> 00:08:58,660
HEH. YEAH.

171
00:09:10,380 --> 00:09:12,710
HI, HONEY.

172
00:09:13,840 --> 00:09:16,090
LOOK WHAT I GOT FREE
AT THE CHECKOUT.

173
00:09:16,300 --> 00:09:18,260
IT'S A CHEF'S PAL.

174
00:09:18,470 --> 00:09:20,800
IT'S A DICER, GRATER,
PEELER--ALL IN ONE.

175
00:09:21,010 --> 00:09:23,930
NEVER NEEDS SHARPENING,
DISHWASHER SAFE.

176
00:09:24,270 --> 00:09:26,520
WOW.

177
00:09:26,520 --> 00:09:28,940
THAT'S AMAZING.

178
00:09:29,440 --> 00:09:31,440
Meryl: TRUMAN...

179
00:09:31,650 --> 00:09:34,110
YOU MISSED A SPOT.

180
00:09:35,690 --> 00:09:37,200
OH, JESUS.

181
00:09:37,400 --> 00:09:39,740
[LAWN MOWER]

182
00:09:46,120 --> 00:09:47,210
MMM.

183
00:09:47,410 --> 00:09:49,960
  THAT  IS A BEER.

184
00:09:51,380 --> 00:09:54,090
YOU KNOW, I'M THINKING
ABOUT GETTING OUT, MARLON.

185
00:09:54,300 --> 00:09:55,090
YEAH?

186
00:09:55,300 --> 00:09:56,380
OUT OF WHAT?

187
00:09:56,590 --> 00:09:57,510
OUT OF MY JOB,

188
00:09:57,720 --> 00:09:59,180
  OUT OF SEAHAVEN.

189
00:09:59,380 --> 00:10:00,470
OFF THIS ISLAND. OUT.

190
00:10:00,680 --> 00:10:01,050
OUT OF YOUR JOB?

191
00:10:01,300 --> 00:10:02,510
WHAT THE HELL'S WRONG
WITH YOUR JOB?

192
00:10:02,720 --> 00:10:04,510
YOU HAVE A GREAT JOB,
TRUMAN.

193
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:06,560
YOU HAVE A DESK JOB.

194
00:10:06,770 --> 00:10:09,310
I'D KILL FOR A DESK JOB.

195
00:10:11,900 --> 00:10:12,190
HERE YOU GO.

196
00:10:12,400 --> 00:10:14,610
YOU SHOULD TRY STOCKING
VENDING MACHINES FOR A LIVING.

197
00:10:14,820 --> 00:10:15,400
NO, THANKS.

198
00:10:15,610 --> 00:10:16,610
NOW, THERE'S EXCITEMENT.

199
00:10:16,820 --> 00:10:17,860
[BOTH LAUGH]

200
00:10:18,070 --> 00:10:19,360
DON'T YOU EVER
GET ANTSY?

201
00:10:19,570 --> 00:10:21,950
ITCHY FEET?

202
00:10:22,660 --> 00:10:25,120
WHERE'S THERE TO GO?

203
00:10:26,040 --> 00:10:26,790
FIJI.

204
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:28,370
[LAUGHS]

205
00:10:28,580 --> 00:10:29,710
WHERE THE HELL'S FIJI?

206
00:10:29,920 --> 00:10:32,330
NEAR FLORIDA?

207
00:10:33,920 --> 00:10:36,130
HMM.

208
00:10:36,630 --> 00:10:37,460
SEE HERE?

209
00:10:37,670 --> 00:10:38,340
YEAH.

210
00:10:38,550 --> 00:10:40,930
THIS IS US...

211
00:10:41,380 --> 00:10:44,100
AND ALL THE WAY
AROUND HERE...

212
00:10:44,600 --> 00:10:45,890
FIJI.

213
00:10:46,100 --> 00:10:47,430
YOU CAN'T GET
ANY FURTHER AWAY

214
00:10:47,640 --> 00:10:49,940
BEFORE YOU START
COMING BACK.

215
00:10:50,140 --> 00:10:52,690
YOU KNOW, THERE ARE
STILL ISLANDS IN FIJI

216
00:10:52,900 --> 00:10:55,190
WHERE NO HUMAN BEING
HAS EVER SET FOOT.

217
00:10:55,400 --> 00:10:57,650
WHOO.

218
00:10:58,530 --> 00:11:01,240
SO, WHEN ARE YOU
GOING TO GO?

219
00:11:03,490 --> 00:11:05,990
IT'S NOT THAT SIMPLE.

220
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:07,700
  IT TAKES...

221
00:11:07,910 --> 00:11:09,250
MONEY,

222
00:11:09,450 --> 00:11:10,540
PLANNING.

223
00:11:10,750 --> 00:11:13,290
I CAN'T JUST UP AND GO.

224
00:11:14,170 --> 00:11:15,460
RIGHT.

225
00:11:15,670 --> 00:11:16,500
I'M GOING TO DO IT.

226
00:11:16,710 --> 00:11:18,760
DON'T WORRY ABOUT THAT.

227
00:11:18,960 --> 00:11:21,800
BONUS TIME IS JUST
AROUND THE CORNER.

228
00:11:23,640 --> 00:11:25,890
HMM.

229
00:11:26,430 --> 00:11:28,310
HEY, YOU COMING
FOR A DRINK?

230
00:11:28,520 --> 00:11:31,020
NO. I CAN'T TONIGHT.

231
00:11:49,080 --> 00:11:51,120
I DON'T LIKE THE LOOK
OF THAT WEATHER, SON.

232
00:11:51,330 --> 00:11:52,330
I THINK WE SHOULD
HEAD BACK.

233
00:11:52,540 --> 00:11:53,670
OH, NO, DAD.
NOT YET.

234
00:11:53,870 --> 00:11:54,960
NO, COME ON.
WE SHOULD GO BACK.

235
00:11:55,170 --> 00:11:56,920
A BIT FARTHER.
LISTEN--

236
00:11:57,130 --> 00:11:58,000
PLEASE?

237
00:11:58,210 --> 00:11:59,550
OK.

238
00:11:59,750 --> 00:12:01,010
YES.

239
00:12:01,260 --> 00:12:02,420
[THUNDER]

240
00:12:02,630 --> 00:12:04,890
DADDY!

241
00:12:38,080 --> 00:12:40,420
[THUNDER]

242
00:12:42,760 --> 00:12:44,970
OHH!

243
00:13:01,650 --> 00:13:03,360
HA HA HA HA HA HA!

244
00:13:03,570 --> 00:13:04,780
 OH 

245
00:13:04,990 --> 00:13:07,320
[THUNDER]

246
00:13:18,330 --> 00:13:21,170
YOU'RE SOAKED.
WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?

247
00:13:21,420 --> 00:13:23,590
I FIGURE IF WE CAN
SCRAPE TOGETHER 8,000--

248
00:13:23,800 --> 00:13:25,170
EVERY TIME YOU AND MARLON
GET TOGETHER--

249
00:13:25,380 --> 00:13:27,590
WE CAN BUM AROUND THE WORLD
FOR A YEAR ON THAT.

250
00:13:27,800 --> 00:13:28,550
AND THEN WHAT, TRUMAN?

251
00:13:28,760 --> 00:13:30,970
WE'D BE WHERE WE WERE
5 YEARS AGO.

252
00:13:31,220 --> 00:13:33,970
YOU'RE TALKING
LIKE A TEENAGER.

253
00:13:34,310 --> 00:13:35,890
WELL, MAYBE I FEEL
LIKE A TEENAGER.

254
00:13:36,100 --> 00:13:38,900
WE HAVE MORTGAGE PAYMENTS,
TRUMAN.

255
00:13:39,650 --> 00:13:40,560
WE HAVE CAR PAYMENTS.

256
