GET OUT OF HERE.
COME AND FIND ME.

513
00:27:24,720 --> 00:27:25,350
DON'T WORRY.

514
00:27:25,560 --> 00:27:26,770
WE'RE GOING
TO FIJI.

515
00:27:26,970 --> 00:27:28,980
FIJI. WE'RE
MOVING TO FIJI.

516
00:27:29,180 --> 00:27:31,480
FIJI?

517
00:27:41,950 --> 00:27:42,910
SYLVIA!

518
00:27:43,110 --> 00:27:45,370
HEY!

519
00:27:53,670 --> 00:27:55,670
WHY DIDN'T HE JUST
FOLLOW HER TO FIJI?

520
00:27:55,880 --> 00:27:58,670
HIS MOTHER GOT SICK,
REALLY SICK.

521
00:27:58,960 --> 00:28:01,090
HE COULDN'T LEAVE HER.
HE'S KIND.

522
00:28:01,300 --> 00:28:02,800
MAYBE HE'S TOO KIND.

523
00:28:03,010 --> 00:28:06,010
I CAN'T BELIEVE HE MARRIED
MERYL ON THE REBOUND.

524
00:28:06,470 --> 00:28:07,890
EXCUSE ME.

525
00:28:08,100 --> 00:28:08,470
COME ON, SAL.

526
00:28:08,680 --> 00:28:11,690
WE'VE ALREADY GOT THIS
ON THE GREATEST HITS TAPE.

527
00:28:11,810 --> 00:28:14,270
CAN I BORROW THAT?

528
00:29:00,030 --> 00:29:02,570
CLOSE, BUT NO CIGAR.

529
00:29:03,950 --> 00:29:06,240
[SIGHS]

530
00:29:29,600 --> 00:29:31,970
Radio Announcer:
AND IT'S ANOTHER BEAUTIFUL DAY

531
00:29:32,180 --> 00:29:32,640
IN PARADISE, FOLKS,

532
00:29:32,850 --> 00:29:35,940
BUT DON'T FORGET TO BUCKLE UP
OUT THERE IN RADIO LAND.

533
00:29:35,980 --> 00:29:38,400
[MALFUNCTIONS] REMEM--
GOOD DRIVER--GOOD--GOOD--GOOD.

534
00:29:38,610 --> 00:29:41,440
  GOOD--GOOD--GOOD--
GOOD--GOOD.

535
00:29:41,780 --> 00:29:43,030
DRIVER--GOOD--DRIVER--GOOD.

536
00:29:43,240 --> 00:29:44,490
GOOD--GOOD--GOOD.

537
00:29:44,690 --> 00:29:46,030
[STATIC]

538
00:29:46,240 --> 00:29:49,120
Man: WAIT FOR THE CUE.
WAIT FOR THE CUE.

539
00:29:49,450 --> 00:29:50,240
[STATIC]

540
00:29:50,450 --> 00:29:51,740
Man: STAND BY, ONE.

541
00:29:51,950 --> 00:29:53,080
[STATIC]

542
00:29:53,290 --> 00:29:55,910
Man: COUNTDOWN TO ACTION.

543
00:29:55,910 --> 00:29:56,620
STAND BY, ONE.

544
00:29:56,830 --> 00:29:59,540
HE'S HEADING WEST
ON STEWART.

545
00:30:00,960 --> 00:30:01,750
STAND BY, ALL EXTRAS.

546
00:30:01,960 --> 00:30:04,300
HE'LL BE ON YOU
IN ABOUT 90 SECONDS.

547
00:30:04,510 --> 00:30:06,170
PROPS, MAKE SURE
THE COFFEE'S HOT.

548
00:30:06,380 --> 00:30:09,390
OK, HE'S MAKING HIS TURN
ONTO LANCASTER SQUARE.

549
00:30:12,430 --> 00:30:12,600
AAH!

550
00:30:12,810 --> 00:30:14,020
Man on radio: OH, MY GOD.
HE NEARLY HIT HER.

551
00:30:14,220 --> 00:30:16,520
SOMETHING'S WRONG.
CHANGE FREQUENCIES.

552
00:30:16,730 --> 00:30:19,190
[LOUD FEEDBACK]

553
00:30:21,360 --> 00:30:23,440
Radio announcer: OUCH.
SORRY ABOUT THAT, FOLKS.

554
00:30:23,650 --> 00:30:25,610
I GUESS WE PICKED UP A POLICE
FREQUENCY OR SOMETHING.

555
00:30:25,820 --> 00:30:28,910
IT SOMETIMES HAPPENS,
AND IT CAN DRIVE YOU CRAZY.

556
00:30:28,950 --> 00:30:30,820
OK, IT'S CLASSICAL CLIVE
BACK IN HERE,

557
00:30:31,030 --> 00:30:32,950
AND WE'VE STILL GOT
SOME GREAT MUSIC UP AHEAD,

558
00:30:33,160 --> 00:30:34,200
BUT HEY,
DON'T FORGET TO BUCKLE UP.

559
00:30:34,410 --> 00:30:37,460
REMEMBER SAFETY.
A GOOD DRIVER IS A SAFE DRIVER.

560
00:30:37,540 --> 00:30:40,210
A SAFE DRIVER IS WHAT?
YES.

561
00:30:40,960 --> 00:30:43,420
[TURNS RADIO OFF]

562
00:30:56,600 --> 00:30:59,020
MORNING, MA'AM.

563
00:32:17,140 --> 00:32:19,640
[ELECTRICAL BUZZING]

564
00:32:37,030 --> 00:32:37,620
I LOVE THAT IDEA.

565
00:32:37,830 --> 00:32:38,870
IT'S PRETTY COOL,
ISN'T IT?

566
00:32:39,080 --> 00:32:41,500
YEAH, I LOVE IT.

567
00:32:43,460 --> 00:32:45,920
[SPEAKING SPANISH]

568
00:33:43,520 --> 00:33:44,270
[DING]

569
00:33:44,480 --> 00:33:45,020
CAN I HELP?

570
00:33:45,230 --> 00:33:46,480
YEAH. I HAVE
AN APPOINTMENT

571
00:33:46,690 --> 00:33:47,690
AT GABLE
ENTERPRISES.

572
00:33:47,900 --> 00:33:50,360
THAT'S IMPOSSIBLE.

573
00:33:54,610 --> 00:33:55,400
WHAT'S HAPPENING?

574
00:33:55,610 --> 00:33:56,570
Guard: NOTHING.

575
00:33:56,780 --> 00:33:58,070
JUST TELL ME
WHAT'S HAPPENING.

576
00:33:58,280 --> 00:33:59,950
GOT TO GO, SIR.
WE'RE REMODELING.

577
00:34:00,160 --> 00:34:00,580
NO, YOU'RE NOT.

578
00:34:00,780 --> 00:34:02,240
WHAT ARE THOSE PEOPLE
DOING BACK THERE?

579
00:34:02,450 --> 00:34:03,080
IT'S NONE OF
YOUR BUSINESS.

580
00:34:03,290 --> 00:34:05,910
IF YOU DON'T TELL ME WHAT'S
HAPPENING, I'LL REPORT YOU!

581
00:34:06,120 --> 00:34:08,580
YOU'RE TRESPASSING.

582
00:34:09,290 --> 00:34:11,590
RIGHT.

583
00:34:39,610 --> 00:34:41,280
MARLON!

584
00:34:41,490 --> 00:34:42,030
TRUMAN.

585
00:34:42,240 --> 00:34:42,910
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

586
00:34:43,120 --> 00:34:44,040
[WHISPERING]
I gotta talk to you.

587
00:34:44,240 --> 00:34:45,500
IT'S A BAD TIME, OK?
I'M WAY BEHIND.

588
00:34:45,700 --> 00:34:48,620
I'M ONTO SOMETHING, MARLON.
SOMETHING BIG.

589
00:34:49,080 --> 00:34:49,880
YOU OK?
YOU LOOK LIKE SHIT.

590
00:34:50,080 --> 00:34:52,000
I THINK I'M MIXED UP
IN SOMETHING.

591
00:34:52,210 --> 00:34:52,590
MIXED UP IN WHAT?

592
00:34:52,790 --> 00:34:53,710
THERE'S NO POINT
TRYING TO EXPLAIN IT,

593
00:34:53,920 --> 00:34:56,920
BUT A LOT OF STRANGE THINGS
HAVE BEEN HAPPENING.

594
00:34:56,920 --> 00:34:59,260
[STAMMERING]

595
00:35:01,140 --> 00:35:03,140
THE PEOPLE ON THE ELEVATOR.

596
00:35:03,350 --> 00:35:04,720
THERE WAS
NO BACKING ON IT.

597
00:35:04,930 --> 00:35:06,770
I LOOKED OUT.
THERE WAS PEOPLE THERE.

598
00:35:06,980 --> 00:35:09,230
AND ON THE RADIO
ON THE WAY TO WORK,

599
00:35:09,440 --> 00:35:10,600
IT STARTS
FOLLOWING ME ALONG,

600
00:35:10,810 --> 00:35:12,650
TALKING ABOUT EVERYTHING
THAT I'M DOING.

601
00:35:12,860 --> 00:35:13,320
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN?

602
00:35:13,520 --> 00:35:15,610
TRUMAN, LOOK, THIS IS
ONE OF YOUR FANTASIES.

603
00:35:15,820 --> 00:35:17,240
I THINK
THIS IS ABOUT MY DAD.

604
00:35:17,440 --> 00:35:18,400
YOUR DAD?

605
00:35:18,610 --> 00:35:19,400
I THINK HE'S ALIVE.

606
00:35:19,610 --> 00:35:22,070
YEAH. I'LL TELL YOU
ABOUT IT LATER.

607
00:35:22,280 --> 00:35:23,990
I'm definitely
being followed.

608
00:35:24,200 --> 00:35:26,410
WHO?

609
00:35:27,040 --> 00:35:28,250
IT'S HARD TO TELL.

610
00:35:28,460 --> 00:35:31,330
THEY LOOK JUST LIKE
REGULAR PEOPLE.

611
00:35:34,500 --> 00:35:35,340
HOW ABOUT THOSE TWO?

612
00:35:35,550 --> 00:35:37,090
Truman: I DON'T KNOW.

613
00:35:37,300 --> 00:35:37,590
COULD BE.

614
00:35:37,800 --> 00:35:40,840
It's when I'm unpredictable,
that's--they can't...

615
00:35:44,010 --> 00:35:45,310
Did anything happen?

616
00:35:45,510 --> 00:35:45,760
NO.

617
00:35:45,970 --> 00:35:48,060
Mm-hmm. We gotta
get out of here.

618
00:35:48,270 --> 00:35:48,730
You ready to go?

619
00:35:48,930 --> 00:35:50,270
No. I just
came here. Come on.

620
00:35:50,480 --> 00:35:51,480
I TOLD YOU I CAN'T.

621
00:35:51,690 --> 00:35:53,980
[GROWLS]

622
00:35:55,770 --> 00:35:58,650
YOU'RE GONNA GET BOTH OUR ASSES
FIRED. YOU KNOW THAT.

623
00:35:58,860 --> 00:36:00,400
OK, MAN,
LET'S DO IT.

624
00:36:00,610 --> 00:36:02,110
WHAT?
WHATEVER YOU SAY.

625
00:36:02,320 --> 00:36:03,110
I'M GAME.

626
00:36:03,320 --> 00:36:04,120
Marlon: WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

627
00:36:04,320 --> 00:36:07,370
YES, SIREE. YOUR BIRTHDAY
COMES BUT ONCE A YEAR.

628
00:36:10,330 --> 00:36:13,080
Truman: MAYBE I'M BEING
SET UP FOR SOMETHING.

629
00:36:13,290 --> 00:36:16,090
YOU EVER THINK
ABOUT THAT, MARLON?

630
00:36:16,130 --> 00:36:17,000
LIKE YOUR WHOLE LIFE

631
00:36:17,210 --> 00:36:19,630
HAS BEEN BUILDING
TOWARDS SOMETHING?

632
00:36:19,840 --> 00:36:21,130
MMM, NO.

633
00:36:21,340 --> 00:36:22,930
WHEN YOU WERE
HAULING CHICKENS

634
00:36:23,130 --> 00:36:24,970
IN THE SUMMER
FOR KAISER,

635
00:36:25,180 --> 00:36:26,390
WHAT WAS
THE FURTHEST

636
00:36:26,600 --> 00:36:28,680
YOU EVER GOT
OFF THE ISLAND?

637
00:36:28,890 --> 00:36:30,020
WENT ALL OVER.

638
00:36:30,270 --> 00:36:33,140
NEVER FOUND A PLACE
LIKE THIS, THOUGH.

639
00:36:33,400 --> 00:36:35,020
LOOK AT THAT SUNSET,
TRUMAN.

640
00:36:35,230 --> 00:36:37,070
IT'S PERFECT.

641
00:36:37,270 --> 00:36:39,110
YEAH.

642
00:36:39,320 --> 00:36:41,490
THAT'S THE BIG GUY.

643
00:36:41,700 --> 00:36:43,990
QUITE A PAINTBRUSH
HE'S GOT.

644
00:36:44,200 --> 00:36:46,450
YUP.

645
00:36:48,490 --> 00:36:51,290
JUST BETWEEN YOU
AND ME, MARLON...

646
00:36:52,620 --> 00:36:55,290
I'M GOING AWAY
FOR A WHILE.

647
00:36:55,880 --> 00:36:57,790
REALLY?

648
00:36:58,000 --> 00:36:58,920
YEAH.

649
00:36:59,130 --> 00:37:01,800
Mother: OH, LITTLE ANGEL.

650
00:37:02,340 --> 00:37:04,760
[WOMEN LAUGH]

651
00:37:07,430 --> 00:37:09,890
OH, MY LITTLE CLOWN.

652
00:37:12,520 --> 00:37:13,850
OLD CARROT TOP.

653
00:37:14,060 --> 00:37:16,480
THE BEST PHOTOS.

654
00:37:17,940 --> 00:37:18,650
OHH.
OHH.

655
00:37:18,860 --> 00:37:20,400
WE SHOULD BE GETTING YOU
HOME, MOTHER.

656
00:37:20,610 --> 00:37:23,570
HOLD ON A MINUTE.
HERE'S US AT MOUNT RUSHMORE.

657
00:37:23,700 --> 00:37:26,200
DO YOU REMEMBER, TRUMAN,
WHEN DAD WAS STILL WITH US?

658
00:37:26,410 --> 00:37:27,870
THAT WAS QUITE A DRIVE.

659
00:37:28,070 --> 00:37:30,830
YOU SLEPT
THE WHOLE WAY THERE.

660
00:37:30,830 --> 00:37:31,870
Truman:
IT LOOKS SO SMALL.

661
00:37:32,080 --> 00:37:34,620
THINGS ALWAYS DO
WHEN YOU LOOK BACK, DARLING.

662
00:37:34,830 --> 00:37:35,460
OH, LOOK, TRUMAN.

663
00:37:35,670 --> 00:37:38,380
THE HAPPIEST DAY
OF OUR LIVES.

664
00:37:40,420 --> 00:37:41,510
OH, LOOK.

665
00:37:41,710 --> 00:37:43,630
JEAN, JODIE, JOANNE.

666
00:37:43,840 --> 00:37:45,470
DOESN'T SHE LOOK
BEAUTIFUL, TRUMAN?

667
00:37:45,680 --> 00:37:47,390
WELL, SHE STILL DOES.

668
00:37:47,590 --> 00:37:50,680
AND THERE'S LOTS OF PAGES
LEFT OVER FOR BABY PHOTOS.

669
00:37:51,850 --> 00:37:54,810
I WOULD LIKE TO HOLD
A GRANDCHILD IN MY ARMS

670
00:37:55,100 --> 00:37:55,440
BEFORE I GO.

671
00:37:55,640 --> 00:37:57,980
ANGELA, WE REALLY SHOULD
BE GETTING YOU HOME.

672
00:37:58,190 --> 00:37:58,690
I'LL TAKE HER.

673
00:37:58,900 --> 00:38:00,940
NO, NO, NO.
YOU STAY, RELAX.

674
00:38:01,150 --> 00:38:01,530
ENJOY YOURSELF.

675
00:38:01,730 --> 00:38:03,780
YOUR FAVORITE SHOW
WILL BE COMING ON.

676
00:38:03,990 --> 00:38:06,530
BESIDES, WE HAVE
SOMETHING TO DISCUSS.

677
00:38:06,740 --> 00:38:09,450
A CERTAIN PERSON'S
BIRTHDAY.

678
00:38:09,450 --> 00:38:11,080
OH, I SEE.

679
00:38:11,280 --> 00:38:12,580
TV announcer: AND THERE'LL BE
ANOTHER EPISODE

680
00:38:12,790 --> 00:38:14,500
  OF  I LOVE LUCY
SAME TIME TOMORROW.

681
00:38:14,700 --> 00:38:17,920
  BUT RIGHT NOW IT'S TIME
FOR   GOLDEN OLDIES.

682
00:38:18,210 --> 00:38:20,920
TONIGHT, WE PRESENT
THE ENDURING, MUCH-LOVED CLASSIC

683
00:38:21,130 --> 00:38:23,050
  SHOW ME THE WAY TO GO HOME.

684
00:38:23,260 --> 00:38:25,090
A HYMN OF PRAISE
TO SMALL-TOWN LIFE,

685
00:38:25,300 --> 00:38:27,300
WHERE WE LEARN THAT YOU DON'T
HAVE TO LEAVE HOME

686
00:38:27,510 --> 00:38:29,050
TO DISCOVER
WHAT THE WORLD'S ALL ABOUT,

687
00:38:29,260 --> 00:38:32,180
AND THAT NO ONE IS POOR
WHO HAS FRIENDS.

688
00:38:32,310 --> 00:38:35,230
FULL OF LAUGHTER AND LOVE,
PAIN AND SADNESS,

689
00:38:35,980 --> 00:38:37,350
BUT ULTIMATELY REDEMPTION,

690
00:38:37,560 --> 00:38:39,350
WE SHARE THE TRIALS
AND TRIBULATIONS

691
00:38:39,560 --> 00:38:40,150
OF THE ABBOTT FAMILY.

692
00:38:40,360 --> 00:38:43,320
NOTE THE TOUCHING PERFORMANCE OF
RONALD BRIERLY AS UNCLE BUDDY.

693
00:38:43,530 --> 00:38:45,320
AND THAT SCENE WITH THE BOWL
OF CHERRIES IS GONNA HAVE YOU

694
00:38:45,530 --> 00:38:48,110
SPLITTING YOUR SIDES
WITH LAUGHTER ALL OVER AGAIN.

695
00:38:48,320 --> 00:38:49,490
AND THERE'LL BE TEARS, TOO,

696
00:38:49,700 --> 00:38:52,530
WHEN DAVID AND JENNIFER
ARE REUNITED.

697
00:38:53,030 --> 00:38:55,620
BUT ENOUGH FROM ME.
LET'S JOIN THE ABBOTTS

698
00:38:55,830 --> 00:38:58,290
IN CAMDEN VILLAGE.

699
00:39:16,140 --> 00:39:18,560
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

700
00:39:19,940 --> 00:39:22,360
[RADIO STATIC]

701
00:39:22,770 --> 00:39:23,900
OH.

702
00:39:24,110 --> 00:39:26,610
THANK YOU, SWEETIE.

703
00:39:30,320 --> 00:39:31,910
I NEED TO TALK TO YOU,

704
00:39:32,120 --> 00:39:33,620
BUT LET'S GO OUTSIDE.

705
00:39:33,830 --> 00:39:36,830
OH, SWEETIE, I'D LOVE TO,
BUT I'M REALLY LATE.

706
00:39:37,080 --> 00:39:39,540
WHAT'S YOUR RUSH?

707
00:39:40,040 --> 00:39:40,830
SURGERY.

708
00:39:41,040 --> 00:39:42,750
THERE WAS THAT ELEVATOR
DISASTER DOWNTOWN.

709
00:39:42,960 --> 00:39:44,210
IT WAS ON THE NEWS
LAST NIGHT.

710
00:39:44,420 --> 00:39:46,460
THIS CABLE JUST SNAPPED.
THIS ELEVATOR,

711
00:39:46,670 --> 00:39:48,840
IT JUST PLUMMETED DOWN
10 FLIGHTS.

712
00:39:49,050 --> 00:39:49,930
THE NON-UNION WORKERS.

713
00:39:50,130 --> 00:39:52,140
JUST MONSTERS.
YOU KNOW, THAT BUILDING,

714
00:39:52,340 --> 00:39:53,680
IT'S RIGHT NEXT DOOR
TO WHERE YOU WORK.

715
00:39:53,890 --> 00:39:55,760
CAN YOU IMAGINE IF YOU
HAD BEEN IN THERE?

716
00:39:55,970 --> 00:39:57,600
IT'S NOT EVEN WORTH
THINKING ABOUT.

717
00:39:57,810 --> 00:39:58,600
ANYWAY,
I HAVE AN AMPUTATION

718
00:39:58,810 --> 00:40:01,810
ON ONE OF THE YOUNG
WOMEN IN THAT ELEVATOR.

719
00:40:01,810 --> 00:40:02,980
SHE'S VERY YOUNG.

720
00:40:03,190 --> 00:40:03,860
IT'S VERY SAD.

721
00:40:04,060 --> 00:40:05,900
ANYWAY, WISH ME LUCK.

722
00:40:06,110 --> 00:40:08,820
I'LL CROSS MY FINGERS
FOR YOU.

723
00:40:46,980 --> 00:40:49,110
[BRAKES SQUEAL]

724
00:40:49,320 --> 00:40:51,700
UH, EXCUSE ME.
HI. EXCUSE ME.

725
00:40:51,900 --> 00:40:53,660
MAY I HELP YOU?

726
00:40:53,860 --> 00:40:54,160
OH, UH...

727
00:40:54,360 --> 00:40:57,330
YES. I'M LOOKING FOR MY WIFE,
NURSE BURBANK.

728
00:40:58,620 --> 00:40:59,160
IT'S VERY IMPORTANT.

729
00:40:59,370 --> 00:41:01,790
I'M AFRAID THAT
THAT'S NOT POSSIBLE.

730
00:41:02,000 --> 00:41:03,040
SHE'S IN PRE-OP.

731
00:41:03,250 --> 00:41:04,670
SURE.

732
00:41:04,880 --> 00:41:06,540
OK, FINE.

733
00:41:06,750 --> 00:41:08,130
CAN YOU PASS ALONG A MESSAGE?

734
00:41:08,340 --> 00:41:08,960
I'LL TRY.

735
00:41:09,170 --> 00:41:10,800
CAN YOU TELL HER
I HAD TO GO TO FIJI

736
00:41:11,010 --> 00:41:12,630
AND THAT I'LL CALL HER
WHEN I GET THERE?

737
00:41:12,840 --> 00:41:15,590
WHEN YOU--
WHEN YOU GET TO FIJI?

738
00:41:15,840 --> 00:41:16,470
YOU GOT IT.

739
00:41:16,680 --> 00:41:19,180
FINE. I'LL TELL HER.

740
00:41:19,180 --> 00:41:21,640
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

741
00:41:47,130 --> 00:41:48,290
SORRY.

742
00:41:48,500 --> 00:41:50,800
IT'S OK.

743
00:41:56,550 --> 00:41:58,890
HE'S HERE.

744
00:41:59,390 --> 00:42:02,270
Meryl: I KNOW, I KNOW.
SHH, SHH, SHH.

745
00:42:02,600 --> 00:42:04,890
SCALPEL.

746
00:42:06,690 --> 00:42:08,940
AHEM.

747
00:42:09,730 --> 00:42:12,530
I'M NOW MAKING
MY PRIMARY INCISION

748
00:42:13,820 --> 00:42:16,400
JUST ABOVE THE RIGHT KNEE.

749
00:42:18,160 --> 00:42:20,490
[LOUD CLANG]

750
00:42:22,660 --> 00:42:23,580
NICELY DONE.

751
00:42:23,790 --> 00:42:26,540
THIS ISN'T
GOING TO BE PRETTY.

752
00:42:26,620 --> 00:42:29,210
IT'S JUST
BEAUTIFUL.

753
00:42:29,250 --> 00:42:30,670
BEAUTIFUL JOB.

754
00:42:30,880 --> 00:42:33,800
I'LL JUST LET SOMEONE ELSE
TIDY UP HERE.

755
00:42:58,240 --> 00:43:00,820
I'M SORRY TO KEEP YOU.

756
00:43:00,910 --> 00:43:03,290
OH, THAT'S OK.

757
00:43:04,290 --> 00:43:04,740
HOW CAN I HELP?

758
00:43:04,950 --> 00:43:07,040
I WOULD LIKE TO BOOK
A FLIGHT TO FIJI.

759
00:43:07,250 --> 00:43:10,000
WHEN WOULD YOU LIKE
TO LEAVE?

760
00:43:12,790 --> 00:43:15,050
TODAY.

761
00:43:25,350 --> 00:43:27,310
[BEEP]

762
00:43:27,520 --> 00:43:28,390
[BEEP]

763
00:43:28,600 --> 00:43:30,900
[BEEP]

764
00:43:30,980 --> 00:43:31,650
I'M SORRY.

765
00:43:31,860 --> 00:43:34,820
I DON'T HAVE ANYTHING
FOR AT LEAST A MONTH.

766
00:43:35,530 --> 00:43:36,320
A MONTH?

767
00:43:36,530 --> 00:43:39,070
IT'S THE BUSY SEASON.

768
00:43:40,450 --> 00:43:41,870
YOU WANT TO BOOK THE FLIGHT?

769
00:43:42,070 --> 00:43:44,080
IT DOESN'T MATTER.

770
00:43:44,280 --> 00:43:47,080
I'LL MAKE OTHER
ARRANGEMENTS, OK?

771
00:43:50,250 --> 00:43:52,880
Man:
LAST CALL FOR CHICAGO!

772
00:43:54,090 --> 00:43:56,460
ALL ABOARD!

773
00:43:59,670 --> 00:44:01,430
[WHISTLES]

774
00:44:01,640 --> 00:44:03,970
THANK YOU.

775
00:44:05,890 --> 00:44:08,480
WINDY CITY, HERE WE COME.

776
00:44:09,600 --> 00:44:11,980
HI.
HI.

777
00:44:13,770 --> 00:44:15,320
HELLO.

778
00:44:15,520 --> 00:44:17,730
HI.

779
00:44:17,980 --> 00:44:18,940
Truman: SISTERS.

780
00:44:19,150 --> 00:44:21,660
HEY, MOM, ISN'T THAT--

781
00:44:22,160 --> 00:44:24,780
Mom: SHH.
FACE THE FRONT.

782
00:44:33,040 --> 00:44:35,460
[GEARS GRIND]

783
00:44:38,760 --> 00:44:41,130
[GEARS GRIND]

784
00:44:44,760 --> 00:44:46,680
[GEARS GRIND]

785
00:44:46,890 --> 00:44:48,470
[ENGINE STALLS]

786
00:44:48,680 --> 00:44:49,930
[RADIATOR HISSING]

787
00:44:50,140 --> 00:44:52,940
EVERYBODY OFF.
WE'VE GOT A PROBLEM.

788
00:45:12,580 --> 00:45:15,000
I'M SORRY, SON.

789
00:45:27,550 --> 00:45:29,640
HIS FATHER WAS FROM
CHICAGO, WASN'T HE?

790
00:45:29,850 --> 00:45:32,230
NO. HIS DENTIST
WAS FROM PENSACOLA.

791
00:45:32,430 --> 00:45:33,730
HIS FATHER
WAS FROM DES MOINES.

792
00:45:33,940 --> 00:45:35,850
BUT HOW COME HE WANTS
TO GO TO CHICAGO?

793
00:45:36,060 --> 00:45:39,110
HE'S NOT GOING TO CHICAGO.
HE'S NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

794
00:45:39,320 --> 00:45:41,940
  HE HAS TO HAVE IT OUT
WITH MERYL.

795
00:45:42,150 --> 00:45:44,570
[PLUTO BARKS]

796
00:45:57,500 --> 00:45:59,790
TRUMAN?

797
00:46:03,670 --> 00:46:06,130
HONEY, ARE YOU OK?

798
00:46:06,380 --> 00:46:08,680
GET IN.

799
00:46:10,890 --> 00:46:13,140
TRUMAN.

800
00:46:13,520 --> 00:46:15,770
LOOK.

801
00:46:18,480 --> 00:46:20,610
WHAT?
SHH.

802
00:46:20,820 --> 00:46:21,400
I PREDICT

803
00:46:21,610 --> 00:46:23,240
THAT IN JUST A MOMENT

804
00:46:23,440 --> 00:46:26,200
WE WILL SEE A LADY
ON A RED BIKE,

805
00:46:27,070 --> 00:46:28,660
FOLLOWED BY A MAN
WITH FLOWERS

806
00:46:28,870 --> 00:46:31,490
AND A VOLKSWAGEN BEETLE

807
00:46:31,790 --> 00:46:32,950
WITH A DENTED FENDER.

808
00:46:33,160 --> 00:46:34,660
TRUMAN, PLEASE.

809
00:46:34,870 --> 00:46:37,290
Truman: LOOK.

810
00:46:40,790 --> 00:46:43,130
LADY...

811
00:46:44,050 --> 00:46:46,380
FLOWERS...

812
00:46:46,470 --> 00:46:48,800
Both: AND...

813
00:46:50,300 --> 00:46:52,010
TRUMAN, THIS IS SILLY.

814
00:46:52,220 --> 00:46:53,520
THERE IT IS!
THERE IT IS!

815
00:46:53,720 --> 00:46:56,600
  THERE'S THAT DENTED
BEETLE! YES!

816
00:46:56,940 --> 00:46:59,230
AAAAAAH!

817
00:46:59,270 --> 00:47:01,650
HA HA HA!

818
00:47:02,520 --> 00:47:05,400
DON'T YOU WANT TO KNOW
HOW I DID THAT?

819
00:47:05,440 --> 00:47:06,360
I'LL TELL YOU.

820
00:47:06,570 --> 00:47:07,360
THEY'RE ON A LOOP.

821
00:47:07,570 --> 00:47:08,990
THEY GO AROUND THE BLOCK.

822
00:47:09,200 --> 00:47:09,870
THEY COME BACK.

823
00:47:10,070 --> 00:47:11,120
THEY GO AROUND AGAIN.

824
00:47:11,320 --> 00:47:12,530
THEY JUST GO
ROUND AND ROUND.

825
00:47:12,740 --> 00:47:13,080
ROUND AND ROUND.

826
00:47:13,290 --> 00:47:16,370
I INVITED RITA AND MARLON
FOR A BARBECUE ON SUNDAY.

827
00:47:17,210 --> 00:47:17,750
I WON'T BE HERE
SUNDAY.

828
00:47:17,960 --> 00:47:20,670
AND I NEED YOU TO REMIND ME
THAT WE NEED MORE CHARCOAL.

829
00:47:20,880 --> 00:47:23,800
ARE YOU LISTENING
TO A WORD I'M SAYING?

830
00:47:24,170 --> 00:47:27,130
YOU'RE UPSET BECAUSE
YOU WANT TO GO TO FIJI.

831
00:47:28,050 --> 00:47:30,140
IS THAT IT?

832
00:47:30,340 --> 00:47:32,680
OK, OK, GO.

833
00:47:35,680 --> 00:47:38,560
I THINK YOU SHOULD SAVE
FOR A FEW MONTHS

834
00:47:38,560 --> 00:47:41,060
AND THEN GO. THERE.

835
00:47:41,310 --> 00:47:43,060
ARE YOU HAPPY NOW?

836
00:47:43,270 --> 00:47:45,900
I WANT TO GO TAKE A SHOWER.

837
00:47:46,740 --> 00:47:47,860
LET'S GO NOW.

838
00:47:48,070 --> 00:47:49,530
I'M READY TO GO NOW.
WHY WAIT?

839
00:47:49,740 --> 00:47:50,780
EARLY BIRD
GATHERS NO MOSS.

840
00:47:50,990 --> 00:47:53,870
ROLLING STONE CATCHES
THE WORM, RIGHT?

841
00:47:54,160 --> 00:47:55,200
[LAUGHS]

842
00:47:55,410 --> 00:47:58,210
Meryl: TRUMAN,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

843
00:47:59,410 --> 00:48:01,670
OH!

844
00:48:03,290 --> 00:48:04,290
TRUMAN!

845
00:48:04,500 --> 00:48:07,340
WHERE SHALL WE GO?
WHERE SHALL WE GO?

846
00:48:08,220 --> 00:48:09,720
TRUMAN, WHERE
ARE WE GOING?

847
00:48:09,930 --> 00:48:13,010
I DON'T REALLY KNOW.
I GUESS I'M BEING SPONTANEOUS.

848
00:48:14,430 --> 00:48:15,640
SOMEBODY HELP ME!

849
00:48:15,850 --> 00:48:17,810
I'M BEING SPONTANEOUS!

850
00:48:18,020 --> 00:48:19,100
Meryl: TRUMAN.

851
00:48:19,310 --> 00:48:19,890
FORGET FIJI.

852
00:48:20,100 --> 00:48:22,310
CAN'T VERY WELL DRIVE
TO FIJI, CAN WE?

853
00:48:22,520 --> 00:48:24,770
NO.

854
00:48:25,230 --> 00:48:27,860
WHAT ABOUT
ATLANTIC CITY?

855
00:48:28,030 --> 00:48:29,900
OH, NO, YOU HATE
TO GAMBLE.

856
00:48:30,110 --> 00:48:30,990
THAT'S RIGHT,
I DO, DON'T I?

857
00:48:31,200 --> 00:48:32,820
SO WHY WOULD YOU WANT
TO GO THERE?

858
00:48:33,030 --> 00:48:34,160
BECAUSE I NEVER HAVE.

859
00:48:34,370 --> 00:48:37,240
THAT'S WHY PEOPLE
GO PLACES, ISN'T IT?

860
00:48:37,450 --> 00:48:40,410
TRUMAN, TRUMAN,
I THINK I'M GONNA THROW UP.

861
00:48:41,000 --> 00:48:43,290
ME, TOO.

862
00:48:50,470 --> 00:48:52,220
BLOCKED AT EVERY TURN.

863
00:48:52,430 --> 00:48:54,930
BEAUTIFULLY SYNCHRONIZED,
DON'T YOU AGREE?

864
00:48:55,140 --> 00:48:57,350
YOU'RE BLAMING ME
FOR THE TRAFFIC?

865
00:48:57,560 --> 00:48:59,890
SHOULD I?

866
00:49:05,440 --> 00:49:07,770
TRUMAN...

867
00:49:07,980 --> 00:49:09,900
LET'S GO HOME.

868
00:49:10,110 --> 00:49:10,860
YOU'RE RIGHT.

869
00:49:11,070 --> 00:49:12,360
WE COULD BE STUCK
HERE FOR HOURS.

870
00:49:12,570 --> 00:49:15,320
IT COULD BE LIKE THIS
ALL THE WAY TO ATLANTIC CITY.

871
00:49:15,530 --> 00:49:17,530
LET'S GO BACK.

872
00:49:17,740 --> 00:49:20,660
I'M SORRY. I DON'T KNOW
WHAT GOT INTO ME.

873
00:49:24,500 --> 00:49:27,250
Meryl: CAN YOU
PLEASE SLOW DOWN?

874
00:49:27,590 --> 00:49:30,010
YES, I CAN.

875
00:49:30,960 --> 00:49:32,420
TRUMAN! TRUMAN!
THAT'S OUR TURNOFF!

876
00:49:32,630 --> 00:49:33,720
I CHANGED MY MIND AGAIN.

877
00:49:33,930 --> 00:49:35,800
WHAT'S NEW ORLEANS LIKE
THIS TIME OF YEAR?

878
00:49:36,010 --> 00:49:38,680
MARDI GRAS! WHOO!
HA HA HA!

879
00:49:39,350 --> 00:49:41,060
[HONKING]

880
00:49:41,270 --> 00:49:43,520
WHOO!

881
00:49:43,640 --> 00:49:46,610
LOOK, MERYL, SAME ROAD,
NO CARS. IT'S MAGIC.

882
00:49:49,820 --> 00:49:50,400
HA HA HA!

883
00:49:50,610 --> 00:49:52,860
YOU LET ME OUT. YOU'RE
NOT RIGHT IN THE HEAD.

884
00:49:53,070 --> 00:49:55,240
YOU WANT TO DESTROY
YOURSELF, DO IT ON YOUR OWN.

885
00:49:55,450 --> 00:49:58,240
I THINK I'D LIKE
A LITTLE COMPANY.

886
00:50:04,710 --> 00:50:06,250
OH, TRUMAN...

887
00:50:06,460 --> 00:50:09,090
YOU KNEW
THIS WOULD HAPPEN.

888
00:50:09,590 --> 00:50:12,550
  YOU KNOW YOU CAN'T
DRIVE OVER WATER.

889
00:50:12,710 --> 00:50:15,550
LET'S GO HOME
WHERE YOU'LL FEEL SAFE.

890
00:50:18,390 --> 00:50:19,350
GIVE ME YOUR HAND.

891
00:50:19,550 --> 00:50:21,180
SWEETIE--

892
00:50:21,390 --> 00:50:23,180
DRIVE.

893
00:50:23,390 --> 00:50:24,310
TRUMAN!

894
00:50:24,520 --> 00:50:27,650
WE SHOULDN'T BE DOING THIS!
WE'RE BREAKING THE LAW!

895
00:50:27,810 --> 00:50:29,480
OH, MY!
YOU CAN DO IT!

896
00:50:29,690 --> 00:50:31,020
PLEASE, DON'T!

897
00:50:31,230 --> 00:50:33,030
YOU CAN MAKE IT!
TRUMAN!

898
00:50:33,240 --> 00:50:34,320
AAH! OH, WE'RE OVER!

899
00:50:34,530 --> 00:50:37,490
WE'RE OVER THE BRIDGE!
WE'RE OVER THE BRIDGE!

900
00:50:37,530 --> 00:50:37,860
WE'RE OVER?

901
00:50:38,070 --> 00:50:40,160
WE'RE OVER THE BRIDGE.
WE'RE OVER THE BRIDGE.

902
00:50:40,370 --> 00:50:41,120
WE'RE OVER!

903
00:50:41,330 --> 00:50:43,700
HA HA HA HA!

904
00:50:46,500 --> 00:50:48,420
TRUMAN! WHAT
ABOUT THAT SIGN?

905
00:50:48,630 --> 00:50:51,210
THEY'RE EXAGGERATING.
WE'LL BE FINE.

906
00:50:51,420 --> 00:50:54,340
  EXAGGERATING?
DO YOU BELIEVE THAT?

907
00:50:55,260 --> 00:50:57,590
[YELLING]

908
00:50:57,630 --> 00:51:00,550
OH, MY! OH, MY!
TRUMAN, WE'RE ON FIRE!

909
00:51:00,760 --> 00:51:01,760
IT'S OK.
WE'RE ON FIRE!

910
00:51:01,970 --> 00:51:04,100
  IT'S OK.
IT'S JUST SMOKE.

911
00:51:04,310 --> 00:51:05,680
YOU OK?
YES.

912
00:51:05,890 --> 00:51:07,770
WANT TO DO IT AGAIN?
NO!

913
00:51:07,980 --> 00:51:08,810
HA HA HA HA!

914
00:51:09,020 --> 00:51:11,610
TRUMAN, STOP!
OH, GOD!

915
00:51:12,730 --> 00:51:12,900
OH!

916
00:51:13,110 --> 00:51:14,900
SO, WHAT ARE WE GOING
TO DO FOR MONEY

917
00:51:15,110 --> 00:51:17,700
  WHEN WE GET
TO NEW ORLEANS?

918
00:51:17,900 --> 00:51:20,620
I HAVE MY SEAHAVEN
BANK CARD.

919
00:51:21,120 --> 00:51:24,240
WE'RE JUST GOING TO EAT
INTO OUR SAVINGS, IS THAT IT?

920
00:51:25,540 --> 00:51:28,120
I'M GOING TO HAVE TO CALL
YOUR MOTHER WHEN WE GET THERE.

921
00:51:28,330 --> 00:51:29,460
SHE'S GOING
TO BE WORRIED SICK.

922
00:51:29,670 --> 00:51:32,630
I DON'T KNOW HOW
SHE'S GOING TO TAKE THIS.

923
00:51:44,680 --> 00:51:46,020
WHAT NOW?

924
00:51:46,220 --> 00:51:49,190
Loudspeaker: RED ALERT!
THIS IS A RED ALERT!

925
00:51:49,690 --> 00:51:50,940
[PEOPLE YELLING]

926
00:51:51,150 --> 00:51:52,110
[CAR HORNS HONKING]

927
00:51:52,310 --> 00:51:54,940
TRUMAN, IT LOOKS LIKE
A LEAK AT THE PLANT.

928
00:51:55,150 --> 00:51:57,070
BACK UP! BACK UP!
LEAK AT THE PLANT.

929
00:51:57,280 --> 00:51:58,450
WE HAD TO SHUT HER DOWN.

930
00:51:58,650 --> 00:51:59,910
IS THERE
ANY WAY AROUND?

931
00:52:00,110 --> 00:52:00,950
WHOLE AREA'S
BEING EVACUATED.

932
00:52:01,160 --> 00:52:02,450
IS THERE
ANYTHING I CAN DO?

933
00:52:02,660 --> 00:52:03,120
NO, MA'AM.

934
00:52:03,330 --> 00:52:04,120
THANK YOU
FOR YOUR HELP.

935
00:52:04,330 --> 00:52:06,950
YOU'RE WELCOME,
TRUMAN.

936
00:52:07,950 --> 00:52:10,250
TRUMAN.

937
00:52:12,080 --> 00:52:14,000
TRUMAN! TRUMAN!

938
00:52:14,210 --> 00:52:16,210
TRUMAN, COME BACK!

939
00:52:16,420 --> 00:52:19,090
TRUMAN! TRUMAN!
STOP HIM!

940
00:52:19,630 --> 00:52:20,970
UNH!

941
00:52:21,180 --> 00:52:21,890
TRUMAN!

942
00:52:22,090 --> 00:52:23,720
[WHISTLES BLOWING]

943
00:52:23,930 --> 00:52:26,390
HEAD TO THE LEFT!

944
00:52:32,100 --> 00:52:34,400
AAH! AAH!

945
00:52:40,950 --> 00:52:43,280
STAY AWAY!

946
00:52:47,290 --> 00:52:48,290
UNH! AAH!

947
00:52:48,500 --> 00:52:50,790
UNH! NO!

948
00:52:51,160 --> 00:52:52,750
NO!

949
00:52:52,960 --> 00:52:54,580
Radio:
...NOW IN CUSTODY.

950
00:52:54,790 --> 00:52:57,250
[TRUMAN GROANING]

951
00:52:57,340 --> 00:52:59,710
THANK YOU BOTH SO MUCH
FOR YOUR HELP.

952
00:52:59,920 --> 00:53:01,300
I REALLY APPRECIATE IT.

953
00:53:01,510 --> 00:53:02,630
HE'S LUCKY TO BE
ALIVE, MA'AM.

954
00:53:02,840 --> 00:53:04,720
NEXT TIME, WE'LL HAVE
TO FILE CHARGES.

955
00:53:04,930 --> 00:53:06,350
I UNDERSTAND.

956
00:53:06,560 --> 00:53:08,470
THANKS AGAIN.

957
00:53:08,680 --> 00:53:11,060
GOOD NIGHT.

958
00:53:27,240 --> 00:53:30,040
LET ME GET YOU
SOME HELP, TRUMAN.

959
00:53:30,580 --> 00:53:33,000
YOU'RE NOT WELL.

960
00:53:34,370 --> 00:53:37,250
WHY DO YOU WANT
TO HAVE A BABY WITH ME?

961
00:53:38,550 --> 00:53:40,050
YOU CAN'T STAND ME.

962
00:53:40,260 --> 00:53:42,380
THAT'S NOT TRUE.

963
00:53:42,590 --> 00:53:44,890
[SCOFFS]

964
00:53:46,470 --> 00:53:49,180
WHY DON'T YOU LET ME FIX YOU
SOME OF THIS NEW MOCOCOA DRINK?

965
00:53:49,390 --> 00:53:51,680
ALL NATURAL COCOA BEANS
FROM THE UPPER SLOPES

966
00:53:51,890 --> 00:53:53,980
OF MOUNT NICARAGUA.
NO ARTIFICIAL SWEETENERS.

967
00:53:54,190 --> 00:53:56,980
WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

968
00:53:57,770 --> 00:53:58,690
WHO ARE YOU TALKING TO?

969
00:53:58,900 --> 00:54:01,900
I'VE TASTED OTHER COCOAS.
THIS IS THE BEST.

970
00:54:02,650 --> 00:54:05,740
WHAT THE HELL DOES THIS
HAVE TO DO WITH ANYTHING?

971
00:54:07,490 --> 00:54:08,830
TELL ME WHAT'S HAPPENING!

972
00:54:09,030 --> 00:54:12,080
YOU'RE HAVING A NERVOUS
BREAKDOWN, THAT'S WHAT.

973
00:54:12,450 --> 00:54:15,210
YOU'RE PART OF THIS,
AREN'T YOU?

974
00:54:18,040 --> 00:54:19,540
TRUMAN!
MERYL!

975
00:54:19,750 --> 00:54:22,300
YOU...ARE...SCARING ME!

976
00:54:22,710 --> 00:54:24,840
NO, YOU'RE SCARING ME, MERYL.

977
00:54:25,050 --> 00:54:27,840
WHAT ARE YOU GOING TO DO?
DICE ME?

978
00:54:28,720 --> 00:54:29,930
SLICE ME
AND PEEL ME?

979
00:54:30,140 --> 00:54:31,810
THERE ARE
SO MANY CHOICES!

980
00:54:32,020 --> 00:54:34,480
AAH! DO SOMETHING!

981
00:54:36,390 --> 00:54:37,690
WHAT?

982
00:54:37,900 --> 00:54:40,440
WHAT DID YOU SAY?
WHO ARE YOU TALKING TO?

983
00:54:40,650 --> 00:54:43,030
NOTHING. I DIDN'T
SAY ANYTHING.

984
00:54:43,240 --> 00:54:44,860
I DIDN'T
SAY ANYTHING.

985
00:54:45,070 --> 00:54:46,280
YOU SAID,
"DO SOMETHING."

986
00:54:46,490 --> 00:54:48,240
NO, I DIDN'T. I WASN'T
TALKING TO ANYBODY.

987
00:54:48,450 --> 00:54:49,570
TALK TO ME!

988
00:54:49,780 --> 00:54:50,120
[BANGING]

989
00:54:50,330 --> 00:54:52,040
I DON'T KNOW ANYTHING!
PLEASE STOP!

990
00:54:52,240 --> 00:54:54,330
STAY WHERE
YOU ARE!

991
00:54:54,540 --> 00:54:56,830
TRUMAN?

992
00:54:58,170 --> 00:54:58,960
TRUMAN?

993
00:54:59,170 --> 00:55:01,880
OH, THANK GOD!
OH, THANK GOD!

994
00:55:04,050 --> 00:55:05,880
[SOBBING]

995
00:55:06,090 --> 00:55:08,130
HOW CAN ANYONE
EXPECT ME

996
00:55:08,340 --> 00:55:11,180
TO CARRY ON UNDER
THESE CONDITIONS?

997
00:55:11,470 --> 00:55:13,680
IT'S UNPROFESSIONAL!

998
00:55:13,890 --> 00:55:16,270
SHH, IT'S OK.

999
00:55:18,100 --> 00:55:20,020
EVERYTHING'S
GONNA BE OK.

1000
00:55:20,230 --> 00:55:21,150
OH, GOD!

1001
00:55:21,360 --> 00:55:23,940
IT'S ALL
GONNA BE FINE.

1002
00:55:25,820 --> 00:55:28,660
I DON'T KNOW WHAT
TO THINK, MARLON.

1003
00:55:32,120 --> 00:55:34,870
MAYBE I'M LOSING
MY MIND, BUT...

1004
00:55:38,370 --> 00:55:41,540
IT FEELS LIKE THE WHOLE WORLD
REVOLVES AROUND ME SOMEHOW.

1005
00:55:43,840 --> 00:55:46,760
THAT'S A LOT OF WORLD
FOR ONE MAN, TRUMAN.

1006
00:55:48,880 --> 00:55:51,680
SURE THAT'S NOT
WISHFUL THINKING?

1007
00:55:51,720 --> 00:55:53,310
YOU WISHING YOU'D MADE

1008
00:55:53,510 --> 00:55:55,520
SOMETHING MORE
OUT OF YOURSELF?

1009
00:55:55,720 --> 00:55:57,520
COME ON, WHO HASN'T
SAT IN THE JOHN,

1010
00:55:57,730 --> 00:56:00,980
  HAD AN IMAGINARY INTERVIEW
ON  SEAHAVEN TONIGHT?

1011
00:56:01,190 --> 00:56:02,310
WHO HASN'T WANTED
TO BE SOMEBODY?

1012
00:56:02,520 --> 00:56:05,570
THIS IS DIFFERENT.
EVERYBODY SEEMS TO BE IN ON IT.

1013
00:56:10,450 --> 00:56:13,530
I'VE BEEN YOUR BEST FRIEND
SINCE WE WERE 7 YEARS OLD.

1014
00:56:14,160 --> 00:56:16,040
THE ONLY WAY YOU AND I EVER
MADE IT THROUGH SCHOOL

1015
00:56:16,240 --> 00:56:19,250
WAS BY CHEATING OFF
EACH OTHER'S TEST PAPERS.

1016
00:56:20,210 --> 00:56:22,830
JESUS, THEY WERE IDENTICAL.

1017
00:56:24,040 --> 00:56:26,880
BUT I ALWAYS FELT SAFE
KNOWING THAT.

1018
00:56:27,630 --> 00:56:29,300
'CAUSE WHATEVER
THE ANSWER WAS,

1019
00:56:29,510 --> 00:56:32,590
WE WERE RIGHT TOGETHER
AND WE WERE WRONG TOGETHER.

1020
00:56:34,140 --> 00:56:37,140
REMEMBER WHEN I STAYED UP
ALL NIGHT IN YOUR TENT

1021
00:56:37,390 --> 00:56:40,230
'CAUSE YOU WANTED
TO PLAY NORTH POLE?

1022
00:56:40,730 --> 00:56:42,060
AND I GOT PNEUMONIA?

1023
00:56:42,270 --> 00:56:43,900
[LAUGHING]

1024
00:56:44,110 --> 00:56:45,860
YOU REMEMBER THAT?

1025
00:56:46,070 --> 00:56:48,990
YOU WERE OUT OF SCHOOL
FOR ABOUT A MONTH.

1026
00:56:54,370 --> 00:56:57,410
YOU'RE THE CLOSEST THING
I EVER HAD TO A BROTHER.

1027
00:57:04,420 --> 00:57:06,630
I KNOW THAT THINGS...

1028
00:57:06,840 --> 00:57:09,300
HAVEN'T REALLY WORKED
OUT FOR EITHER OF US

1029
00:57:09,510 --> 00:57:12,300
LIKE WE USED TO
DREAM THEY WOULD.

1030
00:57:12,470 --> 00:57:13,260
I KNOW THAT FEELING,

1031
00:57:13,470 --> 00:57:16,430
WHEN IT'S LIKE EVERYTHING'S
SLIPPING AWAY...

1032
00:57:17,350 --> 00:57:19,100
YOU DON'T WANT
TO BELIEVE IT,

1033
00:57:19,310 --> 00:57:22,270
SO YOU LOOK FOR ANSWERS
SOMEWHERE ELSE, BUT...

1034
00:57:26,900 --> 00:57:27,690
WELL...

1035
00:57:27,900 --> 00:57:30,780
Christof:
BUT, WELL, THE POINT IS...

1036
00:57:31,820 --> 00:57:34,780
I'D GLADLY WALK IN FRONT
OF TRAFFIC FOR YOU.

1037
00:57:38,540 --> 00:57:40,040
Marlon: WELL...

1038
00:57:40,250 --> 00:57:41,660
THE POINT IS,
I WOULD GLADLY

1039
00:57:41,870 --> 00:57:44,330
STEP IN FRONT OF TRAFFIC
FOR YOU, TRUMAN.

1040
00:57:44,540 --> 00:57:47,500
AND THE LAST THING
I'D EVER DO IS LIE TO YOU.

1041
00:57:50,380 --> 00:57:53,340
AND THE LAST THING
THAT I WOULD EVER DO...

1042
00:57:56,390 --> 00:57:58,760
IS LIE TO YOU.

1043
00:58:00,680 --> 00:58:03,440
I MEAN, THINK ABOUT IT,
TRUMAN.

1044
00:58:03,480 --> 00:58:06,150
IF EVERYBODY
IS IN ON IT...

1045
00:58:07,360 --> 00:58:10,030
I'D HAVE TO BE
IN ON IT, TOO.

1046
00:58:18,740 --> 00:58:21,580
I'M NOT IN ON IT,
TRUMAN, BECAUSE...

1047
00:58:22,330 --> 00:58:24,790
THERE IS NO "IT."

1048
00:58:27,630 --> 00:58:30,550
YOU WERE RIGHT ABOUT
ONE THING, THOUGH.

1049
00:58:31,670 --> 00:58:33,550
WHAT'S THAT?

1050
00:58:33,760 --> 00:58:36,510
THE THING THAT
STARTED ALL THIS.

1051
00:58:51,320 --> 00:58:54,070
YEP. I FOUND HIM
FOR YOU, TRUMAN.

1052
00:58:54,740 --> 00:58:56,950
THAT'S WHY
I CAME BY TONIGHT.

1053
00:58:57,160 --> 00:59:00,080
I'M SURE HE'S GOT
QUITE A STORY TO TELL.

1054
00:59:04,370 --> 00:59:06,710
GO TO HIM.

1055
00:59:12,050 --> 00:59:13,800
EASY ON THE FOG.

1056
00:59:14,010 --> 00:59:15,340
[KEYBOARD CLICKING]

1057
00:59:15,550 --> 00:59:18,050
STAND BY, CRANE CAM.

1058
00:59:18,760 --> 00:59:21,100
CRANE CAM.

1059
00:59:27,940 --> 00:59:30,400
BUTTON CAM 3.

1060
00:59:41,240 --> 00:59:43,830
I NEVER STOPPED BELIEVING.

1061
00:59:46,870 --> 00:59:49,620
Christof:
AND WIDE, CURB CAM 8.

1062
00:59:50,630 --> 00:59:53,000
MY SON! OH!

1063
00:59:53,340 --> 00:59:54,750
MOVE IN
FOR A CLOSEUP?

1064
00:59:54,960 --> 00:59:57,340
NO, NO, NO.

1065
00:59:57,800 --> 01:00:00,550
MOVE BACK AND...
FADE UP MUSIC.

1066
01:00:01,600 --> 01:00:04,010
[MUSIC SWELLS]

1067
01:00:07,520 --> 01:00:09,520
AND NOW GO IN CLOSE.

1068
01:00:09,730 --> 01:00:12,360
ALL THOSE
YEARS WASTED.

1069
01:00:12,560 --> 01:00:15,280
I'LL MAKE IT UP
TO YOU, SON.

1070
01:00:16,030 --> 01:00:17,940
I SWEAR.

1071
01:00:18,150 --> 01:00:20,570
[MUSIC SWELLS]

1072
01:00:24,370 --> 01:00:26,620
DAD.

1073
01:00:27,330 --> 01:00:29,580
YES!

1074
01:00:30,670 --> 01:00:33,000
[LAUGHING]

1075
01:00:37,840 --> 01:00:39,130
BRAVO.

1076
01:00:39,340 --> 01:00:42,180
THAT WAS A REALLY GREAT
EXPERIENCE.

1077
01:00:42,390 --> 01:00:42,970
Tech:
CONGRATULATIONS.

1078
01:00:43,180 --> 01:00:45,100
OK, QUIET DOWN.
LET'S CONCENTRATE.

1079
01:00:45,310 --> 01:00:47,970
Chloe:
THAT WAS GOOD WORK.

1080
01:00:48,100 --> 01:00:48,270
WHOO!

1081
01:00:48,480 --> 01:00:50,310
Tech: LET'S GET
SOME CHAMPAGNE UP HERE.

1082
01:00:50,520 --> 01:00:52,020
CONGRATULATIONS.

1083
01:00:52,230 --> 01:00:54,190
Moses: BRILLIANT, CHRISTOF.
JUST BRILLIANT.

1084
01:00:54,400 --> 01:00:57,150
Roman:
IT JUST BROKE MY HEART.

1085
01:01:00,650 --> 01:01:02,200
WELL DONE, EVERYONE!

1086
01:01:02,410 --> 01:01:04,660
BRAVO!

1087
01:01:21,010 --> 01:01:24,010
Announcer: 1.7 BILLION
WERE THERE FOR HIS BIRTH.

1088
01:01:28,060 --> 01:01:31,020
220 COUNTRIES TUNED IN
FOR HIS FIRST STEP.

1089
01:01:31,560 --> 01:01:34,520
THE WORLD STOOD STILL
FOR THAT STOLEN KISS,

1090
01:01:36,150 --> 01:01:38,780
AND AS HE GREW,
SO DID THE TECHNOLOGY.

1091
01:01:38,980 --> 01:01:39,690
AN ENTIRE HUMAN LIFE

1092
01:01:39,900 --> 01:01:42,950
RECORDED ON AN INTRICATE
NETWORK OF HIDDEN CAMERAS

1093
01:01:43,280 --> 01:01:46,240
AND BROADCAST LIVE AND
UNEDITED 24 HOURS A DAY,

1094
01:01:47,120 --> 01:01:50,120
7 DAYS A WEEK TO AN AUDIENCE
AROUND THE GLOBE.

1095
01:01:51,200 --> 01:01:53,830
COMING TO YOU NOW
FROM SEAHAVEN ISLAND,

1096
01:01:54,040 --> 01:01:57,040
ENCLOSED IN THE LARGEST
STUDIO EVER CONSTRUCTED,

1097
01:01:57,710 --> 01:01:59,340
AND ALONG WITH
THE GREAT WALL OF CHINA,

1098
01:01:59,590 --> 01:02:02,720
ONE OF ONLY 2 MANMADE STRUCTURES
VISIBLE FROM SPACE,

1099
01:02:04,130 --> 01:02:06,760
NOW IN ITS 30th GREAT YEAR,

1100
01:02:07,760 --> 01:02:10,060
IT'S...

1101
01:02:13,390 --> 01:02:15,600
WHAT A WEEK IT'S BEEN.
I DON'T KNOW ABOUT YOU--

1102
01:02:15,810 --> 01:02:17,480
I WAS ON PINS AND NEEDLES
THE ENTIRE TIME.

1103
01:02:17,690 --> 01:02:20,780
HELLO AND GOOD EVENING.
I'M YOUR HOST MIKE MICHAELSON,

1104
01:02:21,150 --> 01:02:22,440
  AND WELCOME TO  TRU-TALK,

1105
01:02:22,650 --> 01:02:24,360
OUR FORUM FOR ISSUES
GROWING OUT OF THE SHOW.

1106
01:02:24,570 --> 01:02:27,490
BUT TONIGHT,
SOMETHING VERY SPECIAL INDEED,

1107
01:02:28,030 --> 01:02:29,740
A RARE AND
EXCLUSIVE INTERVIEW

1108
01:02:29,950 --> 01:02:32,200
WITH THE SHOW'S
CONCEIVER AND CREATOR.

1109
01:02:32,410 --> 01:02:35,500
SO, COME WITH US NOW AS WE
GO LIVE TO THE LUNAR ROOM

1110
01:02:35,830 --> 01:02:38,790
ON THE 221st FLOOR
OF THE OMNI CAM ECHOSPHERE,

1111
01:02:39,340 --> 01:02:42,460
WHERE WE'LL FIND THE WORLD'S
GREATEST TELE-VISIONARY--

1112
01:02:43,470 --> 01:02:45,880
THE DESIGNER AND ARCHITECT
OF THE WORLD WITHIN A WORLD

1113
01:02:46,090 --> 01:02:48,890
THAT IS SEAHAVEN ISLAND--
CHRISTOF.

1114
01:02:48,970 --> 01:02:51,520
BEFORE WE BEGIN,
I'D LIKE TO THANK YOU

1115
01:02:51,720 --> 01:02:54,270
ON BEHALF OF OUR AUDIENCE
FOR GRANTING THIS INTERVIEW.

1116
01:02:54,480 --> 01:02:56,230
WE KNOW HOW DEMANDING
YOUR SCHEDULE IS,

1117
01:02:56,440 --> 01:02:59,560
AND WE ALL KNOW HOW JEALOUSLY
YOU GUARD YOUR PRIVACY.

1118
01:03:00,400 --> 01:03:03,110
THIS, SIR,
IS INDEED AN HONOR.

1119
01:03:03,320 --> 01:03:03,820
DON'T MENTION IT.

1120
01:03:04,030 --> 01:03:06,200
WELL, THE CATALYST FOR
THE RECENT DRAMATIC EVENTS

1121
01:03:06,400 --> 01:03:09,370
ON THE SHOW HAS BEEN
TRUMAN'S FATHER, KIRK,

1122
01:03:09,370 --> 01:03:10,830
AND HIS ATTEMPTS
TO INFILTRATE THE SHOW.

1123
01:03:11,030 --> 01:03:13,290
BUT BEFORE WE GET INTO THAT,
I THINK IT'S WORTH NOTING

1124
01:03:13,500 --> 01:03:16,670
THAT THIS IS NOT THE FIRST TIME
SOMEONE FROM THE OUTSIDE

1125
01:03:16,960 --> 01:03:18,040
HAS ATTEMPTED
TO REACH TRUMAN, IS IT?

1126
01:03:18,250 --> 01:03:20,670
Christof: WE HAVE HAD
CLOSE CALLS IN THE PAST.

1127
01:03:20,880 --> 01:03:23,550
Man: TRUMAN!
IT'S TELEVISION!

1128
01:03:23,840 --> 01:03:24,970
YES!

1129
01:03:25,170 --> 01:03:26,630
YES! I DID IT!

1130
01:03:26,840 --> 01:03:28,090
  I'M ON  THE TRUMAN SHOW!

1131
01:03:28,300 --> 01:03:30,720
Mike: BUT THERE'S NEVER
BEEN ANYTHING TO COMPARE

1132
01:03:30,930 --> 01:03:32,310
WITH THIS MOST RECENT
BREACH IN SECURITY--

1133
01:03:32,510 --> 01:03:35,520
THE FIRST INTRUDER TO BE
A FORMER CAST MEMBER.

1134
01:03:36,770 --> 01:03:37,600
A DEAD ONE AT THAT.

1135
01:03:37,810 --> 01:03:40,810
GOTTA SAY, WRITING KIRK
BACK IN--MASTERSTROKE.

1136
01:03:41,570 --> 01:03:44,610
SINCE KIRK STARTED THIS
CRISIS IN TRUMAN'S LIFE,

1137
01:03:44,650 --> 01:03:47,700
I CAME TO THE CONCLUSION
THAT ONLY HE COULD END IT.

1138
01:03:47,990 --> 01:03:50,490
TRUMAN! TRUMAN! NO!

1139
01:03:50,780 --> 01:03:51,870
[CONSTRUCTION NOISES]

1140
01:03:52,080 --> 01:03:52,950
THAT'S OFF LIMITS!

1141
01:03:53,160 --> 01:03:54,160
WHY? WHAT'S
OVER THERE?

1142
01:03:54,370 --> 01:03:56,250
NOTHING. IT'S DANGEROUS.
THAT'S ALL.

1143
01:03:56,450 --> 01:03:58,170
YOU'VE GOT TO KNOW
YOUR LIMITATIONS, TRUMAN.

1144
01:03:58,370 --> 01:04:00,750
Mike: BUT LET'S REMIND
VIEWERS EXACTLY WHY

1145
01:04:00,960 --> 01:04:03,170
DAD WAS WRITTEN OUT
IN THE FIRST PLACE.

1146
01:04:03,380 --> 01:04:05,130
Christof: AS TRUMAN GREW UP,
WE WERE FORCED

1147
01:04:05,340 --> 01:04:08,340
TO MANUFACTURE WAYS
TO KEEP HIM ON THE ISLAND.

1148
01:04:08,800 --> 01:04:10,470
I'D LIKE TO BE
AN EXPLORER,

1149
01:04:10,680 --> 01:04:12,180
LIKE THE GREAT
MAGELLAN.

1150
01:04:12,390 --> 01:04:12,800
YOU'RE TOO LATE.

1151
01:04:13,010 --> 01:04:15,890
THERE'S REALLY
NOTHING LEFT TO EXPLORE.

1152
01:04:16,060 --> 01:04:18,390
[SNARLING]

1153
01:04:19,940 --> 01:04:23,020
Christof: FINALLY, I CAME UP
WITH KIRK'S DROWNING.

1154
01:04:23,020 --> 01:04:23,770
Mike: MOST EFFECTIVE.

1155
01:04:23,980 --> 01:04:25,650
TRUMAN'S BEEN TERRIFIED
OF THE WATER EVER SINCE.

1156
01:04:25,860 --> 01:04:28,950
Christof: WHEN KIRK READ
THE SYNOPSIS OF THE EPISODE,

1157
01:04:28,950 --> 01:04:31,870
HE WAS DISAPPOINTED
TO SAY THE LEAST.

1158
01:04:32,370 --> 01:04:32,530
JESUS!

1159
01:04:32,740 --> 01:04:35,870
I'M SURE THAT'S WHAT CAUSED
HIM TO BREAK ONTO THE SET.

1160
01:04:36,160 --> 01:04:39,250
BUT HOW DO YOU INTEND TO
EXPLAIN HIS 22-YEAR ABSENCE?

1161
01:04:41,750 --> 01:04:42,170
AMNESIA.

1162
01:04:42,380 --> 01:04:45,380
BRILLIANT. LET'S TAKE
SOME VIEWER PHONE CALLS.

1163
01:04:45,840 --> 01:04:48,920
CHARLOTTE, NORTH CAROLINA,
YOU'RE ON WITH CHRISTOF.

1164
01:04:49,590 --> 01:04:52,010
Man: UH, YEAH,
HI, CHRISTOF.

1165
01:04:52,220 --> 01:04:55,350
I WAS WONDERING HOW MANY
CAMERAS YOU GOT IN THAT TOWN.

1166
01:04:55,890 --> 01:04:57,970
SOMEWHERE IN
THE VICINITY OF 5,000.

1167
01:04:58,180 --> 01:05:00,690
Man: THAT'S
A LOT OF CAMERAS.

1168
01:05:00,890 --> 01:05:03,690
REMEMBER, WE STARTED
WITH JUST ONE.

1169
01:05:03,810 --> 01:05:06,480
HE WAS CURIOUS
FROM BIRTH.

1170
01:05:08,570 --> 01:05:09,400
PREMATURE BY 2 WEEKS.

1171
01:05:09,610 --> 01:05:11,360
ALMOST AS IF HE COULDN'T
WAIT TO GET STARTED.

1172
01:05:11,570 --> 01:05:14,530
Mike: HIS EAGERNESS
TO LEAVE HIS MOTHER'S WOMB

1173
01:05:14,910 --> 01:05:16,280
WAS THE VERY REASON
HE WAS THE ONE SELECTED.

1174
01:05:16,490 --> 01:05:19,040
IN COMPETITION WITH 5 OTHER
UNWANTED PREGNANCIES,

1175
01:05:19,250 --> 01:05:22,250
THE CASTING OF A SHOW,
DETERMINED BY AN AIR DATE,

1176
01:05:22,290 --> 01:05:25,170
TRUMAN WAS THE ONE
WHO ARRIVED ON CUE.

1177
01:05:29,340 --> 01:05:32,510
Mike: INCIDENTALLY, I BELIEVE
TRUMAN IS THE FIRST CHILD

1178
01:05:32,510 --> 01:05:34,720
TO HAVE BEEN LEGALLY ADOPTED
BY A CORPORATION.

1179
01:05:34,930 --> 01:05:35,970
THAT'S CORRECT.

1180
01:05:36,180 --> 01:05:38,180
THE SHOW HAS GENERATED
ENORMOUS REVENUES NOW,

1181
01:05:38,390 --> 01:05:41,640
EQUIVALENT TO THE GROSS NATIONAL
PRODUCT OF A SMALL COUNTRY.

1182
01:05:42,140 --> 01:05:43,770
PEOPLE FORGET IT TAKES
THE POPULATION

1183
01:05:43,980 --> 01:05:45,440
OF AN ENTIRE COUNTRY TO
KEEP THE SHOW RUNNING.

1184
01:05:45,650 --> 01:05:47,360
SINCE THE SHOW IS ON
24-HOURS A DAY

1185
01:05:47,570 --> 01:05:50,820
WITHOUT COMMERCIAL INTERRUPTION,
ALL THOSE STAGGERING REVENUES

1186
01:05:51,490 --> 01:05:53,410
ARE GENERATED
BY PRODUCT PLACEMENT.

1187
01:05:53,610 --> 01:05:55,990
THAT'S TRUE. EVERYTHING
ON THE SHOW IS FOR SALE.

1188
01:05:56,200 --> 01:05:57,580
FROM THE ACTOR'S WARDROBE,
FOOD PRODUCTS,

1189
01:05:57,780 --> 01:05:58,620
TO THE VERY HOMES
THEY LIVE IN.

1190
01:05:58,830 --> 01:06:01,960
Mike: AND ALL OF IT AVAILABLE
IN THE TRUMAN CATALOG.

1191
01:06:02,080 --> 01:06:03,420
OPERATORS ARE STANDING BY.

1192
01:06:03,620 --> 01:06:05,250
CHRISTOF, LET ME ASK YOU,

1193
01:06:05,460 --> 01:06:08,420
WHY DO YOU THINK TRUMAN
HAS NEVER COME CLOSE

1194
01:06:08,800 --> 01:06:11,880
TO DISCOVERING THE TRUE NATURE
OF HIS WORLD UNTIL NOW?

1195
01:06:12,170 --> 01:06:14,050
WE ACCEPT THE REALITY
OF THE WORLD

1196
01:06:14,260 --> 01:06:16,180
WITH WHICH WE ARE
PRESENTED.

1197
01:06:16,390 --> 01:06:18,470
IT'S AS SIMPLE AS THAT.

1198
01:06:18,680 --> 01:06:20,390
THE HAGUE FOR CHRISTOF.

1199
01:06:20,600 --> 01:06:23,060
HELLO? THE HAGUE?

1200
01:06:24,100 --> 01:06:25,190
ALL RIGHT,
WE'VE LOST THAT CALL.

1201
01:06:25,400 --> 01:06:27,360
  LET'S GO TO HOLLYWOOD.
YOU'RE ON  TRU-TALK.

1202
01:06:27,560 --> 01:06:30,190
HI, CHRISTOF. I'D JUST
LIKE TO SAY ONE THING.

1203
01:06:30,400 --> 01:06:31,610
YOU'RE A LIAR
AND A MANIPULATOR,

1204
01:06:31,820 --> 01:06:33,700
AND WHAT YOU'VE DONE
TO TRUMAN IS SICK!

1205
01:06:33,900 --> 01:06:36,820
WELL, WE REMEMBER
THIS VOICE, DON'T WE?

1206
01:06:39,240 --> 01:06:40,240
HOW COULD WE FORGET?

1207
01:06:40,450 --> 01:06:41,750
Mike: LET'S GO
TO ANOTHER CALL.

1208
01:06:41,950 --> 01:06:44,620
NO, NO, NO.
IT'S FINE, MIKE.

1209
01:06:45,120 --> 01:06:48,210
I LOVE TO REMINISCE WITH
FORMER MEMBERS OF THE CAST.

1210
01:06:49,500 --> 01:06:51,460
SYLVIA...

1211
01:06:51,670 --> 01:06:54,720
AS YOU ANNOUNCED SO
MELODRAMATICALLY TO THE WORLD,

1212
01:06:55,050 --> 01:06:58,220
YOU THINK BECAUSE YOU BATTED
YOUR EYES AT TRUMAN ONCE...

1213
01:07:00,810 --> 01:07:02,430
FLIRTED WITH HIM...

1214
01:07:02,640 --> 01:07:03,980
STOLE A FEW MINUTES
OF AIR TIME WITH HIM...

1215
01:07:04,180 --> 01:07:07,400
TO THRUST YOURSELF AND YOUR
POLITICS INTO THE LIMELIGHT...

1216
01:07:08,310 --> 01:07:09,440
THAT YOU KNOW HIM?

1217
01:07:09,650 --> 01:07:11,440
THAT YOU KNOW
WHAT'S RIGHT FOR HIM?

1218
01:07:11,650 --> 01:07:14,740
YOU REALLY THINK YOU'RE
IN A POSITION TO JUDGE HIM?

1219
01:07:14,780 --> 01:07:16,820
WHAT RIGHT DO YOU HAVE
TO TAKE A BABY

1220
01:07:17,030 --> 01:07:19,990
AND TURN HIS LIFE INTO
SOME KIND OF MOCKERY?

1221
01:07:20,080 --> 01:07:22,700
DON'T YOU EVER
FEEL GUILTY?

1222
01:07:23,620 --> 01:07:26,670
I HAVE GIVEN TRUMAN A CHANCE
TO LEAD A NORMAL LIFE.

1223
01:07:29,460 --> 01:07:31,420
THE WORLD...

1224
01:07:31,630 --> 01:07:33,590
THE PLACE YOU LIVE IN...

1225
01:07:33,800 --> 01:07:36,260
IS THE SICK PLACE.

1226
01:07:36,760 --> 01:07:38,800
SEAHAVEN'S THE WAY
THE WORLD SHOULD BE.

1227
01:07:39,010 --> 01:07:40,550
HE'S NOT A PERFORMER.
HE'S A PRISONER.

1228
01:07:40,760 --> 01:07:43,060
LOOK AT HIM! LOOK AT
WHAT YOU'VE DONE TO HIM!

1229
01:07:43,270 --> 01:07:44,270
HE CAN LEAVE AT ANY TIME.

1230
01:07:44,470 --> 01:07:46,940
IF HIS WAS MORE
THAN JUST A VAGUE AMBITION,

1231
01:07:47,140 --> 01:07:50,270
IF HE WAS ABSOLUTELY DETERMINED
TO DISCOVER THE TRUTH,

1232
01:07:52,570 --> 01:07:54,570
THERE'S NO WAY
WE COULD PREVENT HIM.

1233
01:07:54,780 --> 01:07:57,740
I THINK WHAT DISTRESSES
YOU REALLY, CALLER,

1234
01:08:00,910 --> 01:08:02,660
IS THAT ULTIMATELY...

1235
01:08:02,870 --> 01:08:05,790
TRUMAN PREFERS HIS CELL,
AS YOU CALL IT.

1236
01:08:06,660 --> 01:08:08,080
THAT'S WHERE
YOU'RE WRONG.

1237
01:08:08,290 --> 01:08:11,250
YOU'RE SO WRONG, AND
HE'LL PROVE YOU WRONG.

1238
01:08:11,630 --> 01:08:14,050
Mike: WELL, ASIDE FROM
THE HEATED COMMENTS

1239
01:08:14,250 --> 01:08:15,920
OF A VERY
VOCAL MINORITY,

1240
01:08:16,130 --> 01:08:18,680
IT'S BEEN AN OVERWHELMINGLY
POSITIVE EXPERIENCE.

1241
01:08:18,880 --> 01:08:21,180
YES. FOR TRUMAN AND
FOR THE VIEWING PUBLIC.

1242
01:08:21,390 --> 01:08:24,010
WELL, CHRISTOF,
I CAN'T THANK YOU ENOUGH

1243
01:08:24,220 --> 01:08:25,810
FOR GIVING SO GENEROUSLY
OF YOUR TIME TONIGHT.

1244
01:08:26,020 --> 01:08:29,270
I THINK IT'S SAFE TO SAY NOW
THAT THIS CRISIS IS BEHIND US

1245
01:08:29,440 --> 01:08:30,850
AND TRUMAN IS BACK
TO HIS OLD SELF,

1246
01:08:31,060 --> 01:08:33,570
WE CAN LOOK FORWARD TO SOME
EXCITING NEW DEVELOPMENTS?

1247
01:08:33,770 --> 01:08:35,320
WELL, MIKE, THE BIG NEWS

1248
01:08:35,530 --> 01:08:37,570
IS THAT MERYL
WILL BE LEAVING TRUMAN

1249
01:08:37,780 --> 01:08:39,200
IN AN UPCOMING EPISODE,

1250
01:08:39,400 --> 01:08:42,450
AND A NEW ROMANTIC INTEREST
WILL BE INTRODUCED.

1251
01:08:42,450 --> 01:08:42,990
Mike: AHA.

1252
01:08:43,200 --> 01:08:45,540
I'M DETERMINED TELEVISION'S
FIRST ON-AIR CONCEPTION

1253
01:08:45,740 --> 01:08:46,910
WILL STILL TAKE PLACE.

1254
01:08:47,120 --> 01:08:50,170
WELL, ANOTHER TELEVISION
MILESTONE STRAIGHT AHEAD.

1255
01:08:51,080 --> 01:08:52,040
YOU HEARD IT HERE FIRST.

1256
01:08:52,250 --> 01:08:54,420
IT HAS BEEN A SINGULAR HONOR
AND PLEASURE, SIR.

1257
01:08:54,630 --> 01:08:56,130
CHRISTOF...THANK YOU.

1258
01:08:56,340 --> 01:08:58,800
THANK YOU, MIKE.

1259
01:09:59,070 --> 01:10:01,530
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

1260
01:10:15,540 --> 01:10:18,040
HEY, SIMEON.
WHAT?

1261
01:10:21,840 --> 01:10:22,590
IS HE LOOKING AT US?

1262
01:10:22,800 --> 01:10:25,550
JESUS, DO YOU
THINK HE KNOWS?

1263
01:10:25,930 --> 01:10:27,890
HELLO?

1264
01:10:28,100 --> 01:10:29,510
BETTER CALL
CHRISTOF.

1265
01:10:29,720 --> 01:10:32,430
HELLO?
COME IN, MAJOR BURBANK.

1266
01:10:33,310 --> 01:10:35,690
[WHISTLING]

1267
01:10:44,700 --> 01:10:47,160
HA HA!
[SNORTS]

1268
01:10:49,450 --> 01:10:51,580
HE'S BACK
TO HIS OLD SELF.

1269
01:10:51,790 --> 01:10:54,120
THANK GOD.

1270
01:10:54,870 --> 01:10:57,170
[LAUGHING]

1271
01:11:00,340 --> 01:11:03,050
THAT'S AN UNUSUAL
CAT, MY MAN.

1272
01:11:07,640 --> 01:11:09,470
I HEREBY...

1273
01:11:09,680 --> 01:11:12,270
PROCLAIM THIS PLANET...

1274
01:11:15,520 --> 01:11:18,230
TRUMANIA
OF THE BURBANK GALAXY.

1275
01:11:21,020 --> 01:11:23,740
IS HE GOING?
HALLWAY CAMERA.

1276
01:11:25,150 --> 01:11:26,740
THAT ONE'S FOR FREE.

1277
01:11:26,950 --> 01:11:29,240
KEEP UP WITH HIM.
HE'LL MOVE FAST.

1278
01:11:29,450 --> 01:11:32,120
STAND BY,
ALL HOUSE CAMERAS.

1279
01:11:32,410 --> 01:11:33,500
MORNING!

1280
01:11:33,700 --> 01:11:35,580
All: MORNING.

1281
01:11:35,790 --> 01:11:37,000
IN CASE I DON'T SEE YOU...

1282
01:11:37,210 --> 01:11:39,170
All: GOOD AFTERNOON,
GOOD EVENING,

1283
01:11:39,380 --> 01:11:41,800
AND GOOD NIGHT.

1284
01:11:42,840 --> 01:11:44,340
GOOD AFTERNOON...

1285
01:11:44,550 --> 01:11:45,340
GOOD MORNING.

1286
01:11:45,550 --> 01:11:47,680
...EVENING,
AND GOOD NIGHT.

1287
01:11:47,880 --> 01:11:50,510
MORNING.
MORNING, SPENCER.

1288
01:11:50,550 --> 01:11:51,560
HOW'S IT GOING?

1289
01:11:51,760 --> 01:11:53,060
HMM, LET ME CHECK.

1290
01:11:53,270 --> 01:11:55,810
VITAL SIGNS ARE GOOD.

1291
01:11:55,890 --> 01:11:57,020
[BARKING]

1292
01:11:57,230 --> 01:11:58,850
WHOA, PLUTO! WHOOP!

1293
01:11:59,100 --> 01:12:00,190
Both:
GOOD MORNING, TRUMAN!

1294
01:12:00,400 --> 01:12:02,400
OH, LOOK WHO'S HERE.

1295
01:12:02,610 --> 01:12:03,610
BEAUTIFUL DAY,
ISN'T IT?

1296
01:12:03,820 --> 01:12:04,530
EVERY SINGLE DAY.

1297
01:12:04,730 --> 01:12:06,360
THE POLICY--
WE'VE THOUGHT ABOUT IT...

1298
01:12:06,570 --> 01:12:07,610
Both: AND WE'RE
GONNA TAKE IT.

1299
01:12:07,820 --> 01:12:08,820
YOU'RE KIDDING?
Both: NO!

1300
01:12:09,030 --> 01:12:10,620
GREAT! WHY DON'T WE GO UP
TO MY OFFICE RIGHT NOW,

1301
01:12:10,820 --> 01:12:11,530
AND WE'LL SIGN THE PAPERS?

1302
01:12:11,740 --> 01:12:13,490
UH, NEXT WEEK
WOULD BE MUCH BETTER.

1303
01:12:13,700 --> 01:12:14,740
NEXT WEEK WOULD BE BETTER.

1304
01:12:14,950 --> 01:12:16,080
ALL RIGHT.
SEE YOU GUYS.

1305
01:12:16,290 --> 01:12:17,910
OK, BYE NOW.
SEE YOU NEXT WEEK.

1306
01:12:18,120 --> 01:12:19,920
GIVE ME SOMETHING
TO LOOK FORWARD TO.

1307
01:12:20,130 --> 01:12:20,920
YOU GOT IT.

1308
01:12:21,130 --> 01:12:22,790
SEE, THIS ISN'T
ABOUT INSURANCE.

1309
01:12:23,000 --> 01:12:25,300
THIS IS ABOUT
THE GREAT VARIABLE--

1310
01:12:25,510 --> 01:12:27,090
WHEN WILL DEATH OCCUR?

1311
01:12:27,300 --> 01:12:30,090
COULD BE A WEEK,
A MONTH, A YEAR.

1312
01:12:30,890 --> 01:12:33,310
COULD BE TODAY.

1313
01:12:33,760 --> 01:12:36,600
SUNBATHER,
MINDING HIS OWN BUSINESS,

1314
01:12:36,680 --> 01:12:39,900
STABBED IN THE HEART BY THE TIP
OF A RUNAWAY BEACH UMBRELLA.

1315
01:12:40,270 --> 01:12:42,310
NO WAY TO GUARD AGAINST
THAT KIND OF THING.

1316
01:12:42,520 --> 01:12:44,940
[TRUMAN LAUGHS]

1317
01:12:45,230 --> 01:12:46,230
UH, SORRY, EXCUSE ME.

1318
01:12:46,440 --> 01:12:48,860
UH, TRUMAN, THIS IS VIVIEN.
VIVIEN, THIS IS TRUMAN.

1319
01:12:49,070 --> 01:12:51,910
THE TWO OF YOU
ARE GONNA BE NEIGHBORS.

1320
01:12:52,120 --> 01:12:54,330
OH.

1321
01:12:54,910 --> 01:12:56,200
I GUESS WHAT I'M--

1322
01:12:56,410 --> 01:12:59,460
WHAT I'M SAYING IS THAT,
UH, LIFE IS...FRAGILE.

1323
01:13:02,420 --> 01:13:04,000
Lawrence:
VIVIEN, YOUR OFFICE.

1324
01:13:04,210 --> 01:13:04,960
SORRY.

1325
01:13:05,170 --> 01:13:06,130
WHAT'S THAT?

1326
01:13:06,340 --> 01:13:08,880
OH, I'M SORRY.
UH...

1327
01:13:09,340 --> 01:13:09,880
YOU DO?

1328
01:13:10,090 --> 01:13:13,050
OH, GREAT. UH, LET ME
TAKE YOUR INFORMATION.

1329
01:13:15,350 --> 01:13:17,850
[LAWN MOWER BUZZING]

1330
01:13:30,450 --> 01:13:32,910
READY 2. GO TO 2.

1331
01:13:36,450 --> 01:13:38,950
AND BACK TO MEDIUM.

1332
01:13:39,660 --> 01:13:42,000
AND WIDE.

1333
01:13:45,250 --> 01:13:47,550
PSST!

1334
01:13:49,260 --> 01:13:52,130
I WAS JUST TRYING
TO TRAIN THE KID TO...

1335
01:13:53,340 --> 01:13:55,680
NEVER MIND.

1336
01:13:57,220 --> 01:13:59,100
Christof: WHAT'S HE DOING
IN THE BASEMENT?

1337
01:13:59,310 --> 01:14:02,390
HE MOVED DOWN THERE AFTER
MERYL PACKED UP AND LEFT.

1338
01:14:02,640 --> 01:14:03,060
WHY WASN'T I TOLD?

1339
01:14:03,270 --> 01:14:06,270
ANY UNPREDICTABLE BEHAVIOR
HAS TO BE REPORTED.

1340
01:14:06,980 --> 01:14:09,820
UH, HE--HE'S JUST SLEEPING,
I THOUGHT.

1341
01:14:10,030 --> 01:14:11,900
THIS THE BEST SHOT
WE'VE GOT?

1342
01:14:12,110 --> 01:14:12,740
WHAT'S TO SEE?

1343
01:14:12,950 --> 01:14:13,950
WHAT'S ON THE CLOCK CAM?

1344
01:14:14,160 --> 01:14:16,660
IT'S AN OBSTRUCTION--
OBSTRUCTION.

1345
01:14:16,870 --> 01:14:17,660
WHAT HAPPENED DOWN THERE?

1346
01:14:17,870 --> 01:14:20,660
HE WAS JUST TIDYING UP
HIS GARBAGE.

1347
01:14:21,290 --> 01:14:23,000
I WAS GONNA CALL YOU,
BUT HALFWAY THROUGH,

1348
01:14:23,210 --> 01:14:25,000
HE GAVE UP,
AND HE FELL ASLEEP.

1349
01:14:25,210 --> 01:14:27,130
I WANNA CHECK ON
THE SETUPS FOR THE...

1350
01:14:27,340 --> 01:14:28,840
Both: INSURANCE
CONVENTION TOMORROW.

1351
01:14:29,090 --> 01:14:31,460
YES.
YEAH.

1352
01:14:32,130 --> 01:14:33,630
NICE MOVE.

1353
01:14:33,840 --> 01:14:36,260
[TAPS KEYBOARD]

1354
01:14:40,720 --> 01:14:42,060
[BEEP]

1355
01:14:42,270 --> 01:14:44,640
THERE YOU GO.

1356
01:14:53,530 --> 01:14:55,990
ISOLATE THE AUDIO.

1357
01:14:56,530 --> 01:14:58,830
GIVE ME A CLOSEUP
ON HIS TORSO.

1358
01:14:59,080 --> 01:14:59,830
[BEEP]

1359
01:15:00,040 --> 01:15:00,790
[SNORING]

1360
01:15:00,990 --> 01:15:02,750
HE'S STILL BREATHING.

1361
01:15:02,950 --> 01:15:04,830
[SIGHS]

1362
01:15:05,040 --> 01:15:06,460
WHERE'S CHLOE?
YES, SIR.

1363
01:15:06,670 --> 01:15:07,080
CALL HIM.

1364
01:15:07,290 --> 01:15:08,170
WHAT DO YOU
WANT ME TO SAY?

1365
01:15:08,380 --> 01:15:10,710
TELL HIM
IT'S A WRONG NUMBER.

1366
01:15:10,920 --> 01:15:11,880
[CHLOE DIALS PHONE]

1367
01:15:12,090 --> 01:15:14,090
[TELEPHONE RINGS]

1368
01:15:14,300 --> 01:15:15,300
WHAT TOOK YOU SO LONG?

1369
01:15:15,510 --> 01:15:18,390
JUST HAD TO WAIT FOR IT.
THEY WERE BUSY.

1370
01:15:18,890 --> 01:15:19,720
[RING]

1371
01:15:19,930 --> 01:15:20,600
HERE.

1372
01:15:20,810 --> 01:15:22,310
WHAT'S GOING ON?

1373
01:15:22,520 --> 01:15:23,930
I DON'T KNOW. THEY'RE...

1374
01:15:24,140 --> 01:15:24,600
[RING]

1375
01:15:24,810 --> 01:15:25,770
HE CAME DOWN INTO THE ROOM.

1376
01:15:25,980 --> 01:15:27,400
HE DID NOTHING
BUT STAND AROUND FOR A WHILE.

1377
01:15:27,600 --> 01:15:29,230
Christof:
SHUT UP AND WATCH IT!

1378
01:15:29,440 --> 01:15:31,360
THEN WE WENT
TO NIGHTVISION.

1379
01:15:31,570 --> 01:15:32,530
[RING]

1380
01:15:32,730 --> 01:15:33,990
HE'S ASLEEP.

1381
01:15:34,190 --> 01:15:35,570
[SIMEON SCOFFS]

1382
01:15:35,780 --> 01:15:36,530
Christof: THERE!

1383
01:15:36,740 --> 01:15:37,700
STOP IT!
WHAT?

1384
01:15:37,910 --> 01:15:38,660
ZOOM IN.

1385
01:15:38,870 --> 01:15:39,450
ON WHICH?

1386
01:15:39,660 --> 01:15:40,620
UNDER THE CHAIR THERE.

1387
01:15:40,830 --> 01:15:43,250
Simeon: UH-HUH.

1388
01:15:43,830 --> 01:15:46,370
Christof: ENHANCE IT.

1389
01:15:47,290 --> 01:15:48,420
Simeon: IS IT--OH.

1390
01:15:48,630 --> 01:15:49,080
Chloe: OH, MY GOD.

1391
01:15:49,290 --> 01:15:52,250
I...IF--HE COULDN'T HAVE
GONE UP THE STAIRS.

1392
01:15:52,960 --> 01:15:54,590
I DEFINITELY--HE MUST
STILL BE IN THE ROOM.

1393
01:15:54,800 --> 01:15:55,840
GET MARLON
OVER THERE.

1394
01:15:56,050 --> 01:15:56,800
RIGHT AWAY.

1395
01:15:57,010 --> 01:15:59,470
[TIRES SCREECH]

1396
01:16:03,100 --> 01:16:05,520
[TIRES SCREECH]

1397
01:16:12,440 --> 01:16:14,150
Marlon: TRUMAN!

1398
01:16:14,360 --> 01:16:16,070
SURPRISE PARTY!

1399
01:16:16,280 --> 01:16:17,650
OH.

1400
01:16:17,860 --> 01:16:18,490
COME ON, BUDDY.

1401
01:16:18,700 --> 01:16:21,830
I GOT A 6-PACK OF COLD BREWSKIS
WITH OUR NAME ON THEM.

1402
01:16:22,330 --> 01:16:24,450
COME ON, PAL.
COME ON, BUDDY.

1403
01:16:24,660 --> 01:16:25,450
[SQUEAK]

1404
01:16:25,660 --> 01:16:27,960
[SNORING]

1405
01:16:29,290 --> 01:16:31,540
SHIT.

1406
01:16:32,460 --> 01:16:35,380
MARLON, FIND HIM.
HE'S STILL IN THE ROOM.

1407
01:16:39,630 --> 01:16:41,850
COME OUT, COME OUT
WHEREVER YOU ARE.

1408
01:16:42,050 --> 01:16:43,560
THAT'S GOOD.
KEEP IT LIGHT.

1409
01:16:43,760 --> 01:16:46,640
I KNOW YOU'RE IN HERE.
I'M GONNA FIND YA.

1410
01:16:50,650 --> 01:16:53,190
CHECK UNDER THE TABLE.

1411
01:16:53,730 --> 01:16:56,280
THE CLOSET, BEHIND YOU.

1412
01:16:59,740 --> 01:17:01,990
HUH.

1413
01:17:02,700 --> 01:17:03,830
GEE.

1414
01:17:04,030 --> 01:17:06,870
I WONDER WHERE HE
COULD POSSIBLY BE.

1415
01:17:14,250 --> 01:17:17,050
THE LAWN CAM,
GET ME THE LAWN CAM.

1416
01:17:23,510 --> 01:17:25,930
DON'T LOOK IN THE CAMERA.
SAY SOMETHING. KEEP IT GOING.

1417
01:17:26,140 --> 01:17:27,930
KEEP IT GOING.
HE'S GONE.

1418
01:17:28,140 --> 01:17:29,560
CUT TRANSMISSION!

1419
01:17:29,770 --> 01:17:30,770
CUT TRANSMISSION?

1420
01:17:30,980 --> 01:17:33,270
CUT IT!

1421
01:17:33,480 --> 01:17:34,190
[BEEP]

1422
01:17:34,400 --> 01:17:34,940
[AUDIENCE GASPS]

1423
01:17:35,150 --> 01:17:36,400
Man: JESUS!
GOD IN HEAVEN!

1424
01:17:36,610 --> 01:17:38,570
Woman:
EVERYTHING'S BLACK.

1425
01:17:38,780 --> 01:17:39,860
GIVE ME THE PHONE.

1426
01:17:40,070 --> 01:17:42,660
[CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING]

1427
01:17:49,580 --> 01:17:52,290
[SPEAKING
VARIOUS LANGUAGES]

1428
01:17:52,830 --> 01:17:55,710
I DON'T KNOW WHERE HE IS,
BUT HE'S GONE.

1429
01:18:00,880 --> 01:18:01,220
[CLEARS THROAT]

1430
01:18:01,420 --> 01:18:04,090
WE'VE GOT EVERY AVAILABLE
EXTRA LOOKING FOR HIM.

1431
01:18:04,300 --> 01:18:05,890
UH, THE PRINCIPALS
ARE HELPING OUT.

1432
01:18:06,100 --> 01:18:08,220
THE CREW, TOO,
SO EVERY SECTOR'S COVERED.

1433
01:18:08,430 --> 01:18:10,140
WHAT ABOUT PROP CARS?

1434
01:18:10,350 --> 01:18:12,190
YES, THEY'VE BEEN
ACCOUNTED FOR.

1435
01:18:12,390 --> 01:18:13,730
HE HAS TO BE ON FOOT.

1436
01:18:13,940 --> 01:18:15,650
HE HAS THE WORLD'S
MOST RECOGNIZABLE FACE.

1437
01:18:15,860 --> 01:18:18,360
HE CAN'T DISAPPEAR.

1438
01:18:21,860 --> 01:18:24,160
[SIREN]

1439
01:18:45,970 --> 01:18:48,600
[PLUTO BARKING, SNARLING]

1440
01:18:52,930 --> 01:18:54,390
Spencer: GO.

1441
01:18:54,600 --> 01:18:56,690
HUNT HIM. HUNT HIM.
YEAH.

1442
01:18:56,900 --> 01:18:58,060
GO FIND HIM, PLUTO.

1443
01:18:58,270 --> 01:18:59,730
GOOD DOG! GOOD DOG!

1444
01:18:59,940 --> 01:19:01,820
ALL THIS FUSS.

1445
01:19:02,030 --> 01:19:04,740
IF HE COULD JUST
HEAR MY VOICE.

1446
01:19:05,410 --> 01:19:07,740
TRUMAN!

1447
01:19:08,030 --> 01:19:09,450
TRUMAN!

1448
01:19:09,660 --> 01:19:11,240
LET ME TRY.

1449
01:19:11,450 --> 01:19:12,870
TRUMAN!

1450
01:19:13,080 --> 01:19:15,500
IT'S ME! DAD!

1451
01:19:17,290 --> 01:19:19,670
LET'S TALK!

1452
01:19:20,420 --> 01:19:22,800
YEAH, I KNOW.

1453
01:19:23,010 --> 01:19:24,260
JUST ABOUT DONE
WITH THE SQUARE.

1454
01:19:24,470 --> 01:19:27,470
GOT TO GO BACK TO BARRYMORE,
CHECK THE INTERIORS.

1455
01:19:27,680 --> 01:19:28,680
HE'S GOT TO BE IN THERE.

1456
01:19:28,930 --> 01:19:30,100
Simeon:
BARRYMORE, HUH?

1457
01:19:30,310 --> 01:19:30,510
UH-HUH.

1458
01:19:30,720 --> 01:19:32,600
BUT WHAT ABOUT THE COLLEGE?
WHO'S WATCHING THAT?

1459
01:19:32,810 --> 01:19:33,270
I DON'T KNOW.

1460
01:19:33,480 --> 01:19:34,770
SEND SOMEBODY
OVER THERE, OK?

